tags: Pivot-based with Keltner Channel filtering
summary: This is an **asymmetric strategy** with different logic for long and short trades. **Long entries** use pivot support levels with high-to-typical price calculations, while **short entries** use Keltner Channel filtering with previous day's close. The strategy employs **trailing stops** and **time-based exits** with end-of-session liquidation.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• AS_PivotS(2) <= Current High (pivot support breach)
• Current Close > Entry Price (H[6] - 0.5 * |Lowest(H,28) - TypicalPrice|)
• Must be at market open or Friday end-of-session

**SHORT Entries:**
• Previous day's Close <= Keltner Channel upper band
• Keltner based on H[97] with 57-bar lookback and 2.5 std devs
• Current Close < Entry Price (L + 2.6 * TrueRange)
• Must be at market open or Friday end-of-session
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• End of session on Fridays (SetExitOnClose)

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Long: Money management stop at 240 currency units, trailing stop after 125 currency profit
• Short: Trailing stop after 685 currency profit, pivot target at AS_PivotS(3) - 2.7664*TrueRange

**Time Exits:**
• Short trades: Market exit after 7 bars OR (6 bars if profitable) OR (4 bars if unprofitable)
stop_loss_level:
• Long: **240** in **currency** (fixed stop)
• Short: **Trailing stop** starting at 685 currency profit level
take_profit_level:
• Long: **Trailing profit** at 28% of unrealized gain after 125 currency profit
• Short: **Pivot target** at AS_PivotS(3) - 2.7664*TrueRange
time_exit_details: Exit at **end of session** on Fridays, plus **time-based exits** for short trades (4-7 bars)
pattern_details:
**AS_PivotS(2):** Floor trader pivot support level 2
• Meaning: Second-level support calculated from previous session OHLC
• Indicates: Key support area for potential bounces
• Trading use: Long entry trigger when breached upward

**AS_PivotS(3):** Floor trader pivot support level 3
• Meaning: Third-level support (deeper support)
• Indicates: Strong support level
• Trading use: Short trade profit target

**KeltnerChannel:** Volatility-based channel indicator
• Parameters: H[97] price, 57-bar lookback, 2.5 standard deviations
• Indicates: Overbought/oversold conditions
• Trading use: Short entry filter when previous close below upper band

**CloseD(1):** Previous day's closing price
• Meaning: Yesterday's settlement price
• Indicates: Reference point for mean reversion
• Trading use: Comparison against Keltner Channel for short entries
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Asymmetric approach allows different logic for long/short trades
• Multiple exit mechanisms including trailing stops and time exits
• Risk management with fixed stops and profit floors
• End-of-week position clearing reduces weekend risk

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Complex entry calculations may be hard to validate
• No clear trend filter - could trade against major moves
• Short trade logic seems overcomplicated with multiple time exits
• Position sizing is fixed (no volatility adjustment)

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Fixed currency-based stops provide consistent risk per trade
• Trailing stops lock in profits on winning trades
• Time-based exits limit exposure duration
• Weekend gap risk eliminated

**OVERALL:**
This is a **moderately sophisticated strategy** that attempts to capture different market dynamics with longs and shorts. The **pivot-based long entries** are logical for support bounces, but the **Keltner/CloseD short logic** seems less intuitive. Risk management is **adequate but not dynamic**. The strategy would benefit from **clearer trend filtering** and **volatility-adjusted position sizing**.

tags: Mean Reverting Pivot Bounce with Pattern Confirmation
summary: This is a **mean reverting strategy** that uses **pivot point levels** (R1/S1) as reversal zones combined with pattern confirmation. It goes **long on bounces from S1 support** and **short on rejections from R1 resistance**, trading during specific time windows with strict risk management.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Time window: 22:30 to 11:00 (excluding pause 12:00-11:00)
• Price crosses above S1 (support level)
• PatternFast(37) = true (upper shadow > previous upper shadow)
• PatternFast(62) = false (daily range NOT < 1% of low)
• Maximum 1 entry per day

**SHORT Entries:**
• Same time window as longs
• Price crosses below R1 (resistance level)
• PatternFast(37) = true (upper shadow confirmation)
• PatternFast(62) = false (volatility filter)
• Maximum 1 entry per day
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Maximum 5 days in trade
• Flat time at 15:30

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss at 1100 currency units
• Take profit at 4000 currency units
• No breakeven stop (set to 0)

**Time Exits:**
• Exit on close if maximum days reached
• Forced flat at 15:30
time_exit_details: Exit at **15:30** and maximum **5 days** in trade
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(37):** ((highd0-opend0)> ((highd1-opend1)*2.5))
• Meaning: Current bar's upper shadow is > 2.5x previous bar's upper shadow
• Indicates: Significant rejection at higher levels, potential reversal
• Trading use: Confirms selling pressure at resistance

**PatternFast(62):** ((highd0<(lowd0+lowd0*1*0.01)))
• Meaning: High is less than low + 1% of low (very tight range)
• Indicates: Extremely low volatility, compressed range
• Trading use: Used as FALSE condition to avoid dead markets
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Strong risk management with defined stop loss (1100) and profit target (4000)
• Uses proven pivot point levels as reversal zones
• Pattern confirmation reduces false signals
• Time-based filtering avoids problematic market hours
• Daily entry limit prevents overtrading
• Maximum holding period prevents extended drawdowns

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Relies heavily on mean reversion which can fail in strong trends
• Pattern combination may be too restrictive, limiting opportunities
• No breakeven stop management
• Fixed stop/target ratios may not adapt to market volatility

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Excellent position sizing with defined contracts
• Clear stop loss at 1100 currency units
• Profit target provides positive risk/reward (1:3.6 ratio)
• Daily entry limits and maximum days in trade control exposure

**OVERALL:**
This is a **well-structured pivot reversal strategy** with solid risk management principles. The combination of **pivot levels and pattern confirmation** creates a logical framework, though the pattern selection appears quite specific and may limit trade frequency. The **risk/reward ratio is favorable** and time management is comprehensive.

tags: Session High/Low Breakout with Pattern Filtering
summary: A **session-based breakout strategy** that enters long when price breaks above the highest high of the last N sessions and short when price breaks below the lowest low. Uses **PatternFast filtering** to qualify entries and includes comprehensive time/day/month filtering controls.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Price breaks above **longLevel** (highest high of last nSessions)
• **LongEnabled = true**
• Day of week ≠ **NoLongDay** (default 0)
• Month ≠ **NoLongMonth** (default 9 = September)
• **PatternFast(PtnLY)** = true (default 152 = always true)
• **PatternFast(PtnLN)** = false (default 153 = always false)
• Within time window and pause restrictions
• **LastTradeBar ≠ CurrentBar** (prevents multiple entries same bar)

**SHORT Entries:**
• Price breaks below **shortLevel** (lowest low of last nSessions)
• **ShortEnabled = false** (disabled by default)
• Day of week ≠ **NoShortDay** (default 0)
• Month ≠ **NoShortMonth** (default 0)
• **PatternFast(PtnSY)** = true (default 152 = always true)
• **PatternFast(PtnSN)** = false (default 153 = always false)
• Within time window and pause restrictions
• **LastTradeBar ≠ CurrentBar**
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• **Maximum days in trade:** 9 days maximum hold period
• **Flat time:** Exit at market at 15:55 if max days reached

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• **Stop loss:** 60 in currency
• **Take profit:** 200 in currency
• **Breakeven:** Disabled (0)

**Time Exits:**
• **SetExitOnClose** when max days in trade reached
• **Market exit at 15:55** if position held too long
time_exit_details: Exit at **15:55** if max days in trade reached
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(152):** true
• Meaning: Always returns true
• Indicates: No pattern filtering applied
• Trading use: Allows all entries (default setting)

**PatternFast(153):** false (case >152)
• Meaning: Always returns false
• Indicates: Negative filter always satisfied
• Trading use: No blocking condition applied

**Pattern Logic:**
The strategy uses **dual pattern filtering** where PtnLY/PtnSY must be true AND PtnLN/PtnSN must be false for entries. Default settings (152/153) effectively disable pattern filtering, making this a pure breakout strategy.
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• **Comprehensive filtering system** with day/month exclusions
• **Robust session-based breakout logic** using multiple sessions
• **Good risk management** with stop loss and profit targets
• **Prevents over-trading** with LastTradeBar mechanism
• **Flexible time windows** with pause functionality
• **Maximum hold period** prevents runaway losses

**WEAKNESSES:**
• **Short trading disabled by default** (ShortEnabled = false)
• **September long trades blocked** (NoLongMonth = 9) - may miss opportunities
• **Pattern filtering disabled** with default 152/153 settings
• **No volatility or market condition filters**
• **Fixed stop/target ratio** may not suit all market conditions

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• **Moderate stop loss:** 60 currency units
• **Good profit target:** 200 currency units (3.33:1 reward/risk)
• **Position sizing:** Fixed at 1 contract
• **Maximum days limit** prevents extended exposure

**OVERALL:**
A **well-structured breakout strategy** with excellent filtering capabilities, though currently configured as a **long-only system** with pattern filtering disabled. The **comprehensive time/date controls** and **anti-over-trading mechanisms** show sophisticated design, but the strategy would benefit from **enabling short trades** and **optimizing pattern filters** for better market adaptation.

tags: SMA Crossover
summary: This is a **trend following strategy** based on Simple Moving Average crossovers between a 25-period and 47-period SMA. The strategy includes **pattern filtering** using PatternFast conditions and operates within specific session times with comprehensive risk management.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• 25-period SMA crosses above 47-period SMA
• PatternFast(133) = true: (highd1<highd2 or lowd1>lowd2) - Inside bar or higher low pattern
• PatternFast(75) = false: NOT (closed1<(closed2-closed2*2.5*0.01)) - Close not significantly below previous close
• LongEnabled = true
• Not in January or February
• Day of week ≠ NoLongDay
• Month ≠ NoLongMonth
• Within session time (17:00-16:00) but outside pause (12:00-11:00)
• Less than max entries per day
• LastTradeBar ≠ CurrentBar

**SHORT Entries:**
• 25-period SMA crosses below 47-period SMA
• PatternFast(152) = true: Always true condition
• PatternFast(153) = false: Always false condition (impossible to satisfy)
• ShortEnabled = false (shorts disabled by default)
• Day of week ≠ NoShortDay
• Month ≠ NoShortMonth
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Maximum days in trade (6 days) with flat at 15:55
• SetExitOnClose when max days reached

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss at 100 currency units
• Take profit at 650 currency units
• Breakeven at 0 (disabled)

**Time Exits:**
• Flat time at 15:55 when max days in trade reached
time_exit_details: Exit at **15:55** when maximum days in trade reached
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(133):** (highd1<highd2 or lowd1>lowd2)
• Meaning: Yesterday's high below previous high OR yesterday's low above previous low
• Indicates: Inside bar pattern or higher low formation
• Trading use: Consolidation or minor pullback filter

**PatternFast(75):** ((closed1<(closed2-closed2*2.5*0.01)))
• Meaning: Yesterday's close below previous close minus 2.5%
• Indicates: Significant downward price movement
• Trading use: Avoid longs after major drops (used as negative filter)

**PatternFast(152):** true
• Meaning: Always returns true
• Indicates: No pattern restriction
• Trading use: Allows all short entries (when enabled)

**PatternFast(153):** false
• Meaning: Always returns false
• Indicates: Impossible condition
• Trading use: Effectively blocks all short entries
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Clear trend following logic with SMA crossover
• Comprehensive time and session management
• Good risk management with stop loss and profit target
• Pattern filtering to avoid poor entry conditions
• Position sizing and entry limits per day
• Seasonal filters (excludes January/February for longs)

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Short entries are effectively disabled (PatternFast 153 always false)
• SMA crossovers are lagging indicators, may miss trend starts
• No volatility or market condition filters
• Fixed stop/profit levels may not adapt to market conditions
• Pattern 152 for shorts provides no actual filtering
• Long-only bias in trending markets limits opportunities

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Stop loss at 100 currency units provides downside protection
• 6.5:1 reward-to-risk ratio (650 profit vs 100 stop)
• Maximum days in trade prevents extended drawdowns
• Daily entry limits control overexposure

**OVERALL:**
This is a **basic trend following system** with good risk management but **limited short-side functionality**. The strategy appears designed primarily for **long-only trading** with reasonable filters, but the short logic contains a fatal flaw that prevents short entries entirely.

tags: Multi-pattern trend following with unmirrored bias logic
summary: This is a **dual-direction pattern-based strategy** that uses multiple pattern conditions for both long and short entries. It employs **unmirrored bias logic** where different patterns are required for each direction, operating during specific time windows with comprehensive risk management.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• PatternFast(66) must be TRUE
• PatternFast(74) must be FALSE
• Entry time must be 10:00
• Within session window (17:00-16:00)
• Outside pause window (12:00-11:00)
• Maximum 2 entries per day not exceeded
• Long direction enabled and not restricted by day/month filters

**SHORT Entries:**
• PatternFast(152) must be TRUE (always true)
• PatternFast(84) must be FALSE
• Entry time must be 09:00
• Within session window (17:00-16:00)
• Outside pause window (12:00-11:00)
• Maximum 2 entries per day not exceeded
• Short direction enabled and not restricted by day/month filters
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Long positions exit at 09:00 (MyLXTime)
• Short positions exit at 08:00 (MySXTime)

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss at 300 currency units
• Take profit at 800 currency units
• Breakeven disabled (set to 0)

**Time Exits:**
• Mandatory time-based exits for position management
• Different exit times for long vs short positions
time_exit_details: Long exits at **09:00**, Short exits at **08:00**
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(66):** highd0<(lowd0+lowd0*3*0.01)
• Meaning: Current high is less than current low plus 3% of low
• Indicates: Extremely narrow range or gap down condition
• Trading use: Low volatility or bearish momentum setup for long entries

**PatternFast(74):** closed1<(closed2-closed2*2*0.01)
• Meaning: Yesterday's close is more than 2% below the previous day's close
• Indicates: Significant downward price movement
• Trading use: Used as negative filter (must be FALSE) to avoid buying into strong declines

**PatternFast(152):** true
• Meaning: Always evaluates to true
• Indicates: No actual pattern constraint
• Trading use: Allows short entries without pattern restriction

**PatternFast(84):** highd0>(highd1+highd1*0.75*0.01)
• Meaning: Current high exceeds previous high by more than 0.75%
• Indicates: Upward breakout or strong buying pressure
• Trading use: Used as negative filter (must be FALSE) to avoid shorting into breakouts
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Comprehensive risk management with both stops and targets
• Time-based position management prevents overnight exposure
• Multiple safety filters including daily entry limits
• Unmirrored logic allows different criteria for each direction
• Session-based approach with pause periods

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Pattern 152 (always true) provides no real filtering for shorts
• Asymmetric exit times may create unbalanced risk exposure
• Complex pattern combinations may lead to overfitting
• No trailing stop mechanism limits profit capture
• Fixed entry times may miss optimal setups

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Stop loss of 300 currency units provides clear downside protection
• Take profit of 800 currency units creates favorable 2.67:1 reward-risk ratio
• Daily entry limits prevent overexposure
• Time exits ensure positions don't remain open indefinitely

**OVERALL:**
This is a **moderately sophisticated pattern-based strategy** with good risk controls but questionable pattern logic. The use of PatternFast(152) as an always-true condition for shorts suggests incomplete strategy development. **Time-based exits and comprehensive filters** are positive features, but the strategy would benefit from more meaningful pattern conditions for short entries.

tags: Session-based breakout with pattern filtering
summary: A **session-based breakout strategy** that trades breakouts above previous session's high (long) or below low (short) during specific time windows. Uses **pattern filtering** with PatternFast(152) as always-true condition and PatternFast(153) as always-false condition, essentially creating **unfiltered breakouts**.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Buy next bar at previous session **high** (stop order)
• PatternFast(152) = true AND PatternFast(153) = false
• Within trading hours (07:00-22:00, excluding 12:00-11:00 pause)
• Maximum 2 entries per day
• Long trades enabled and not restricted by day/month

**SHORT Entries:**
• Sell short next bar at previous session **low** (stop order)
• PatternFast(152) = true AND PatternFast(137) = false
• Same time and frequency restrictions as longs
• Short trades enabled and not restricted by day/month
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Maximum 5 days in trade (exit at close then market order at 15:45)
• Flat time at 15:45 if max days reached

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 50 currency units
• Take profit: 900 currency units

**Time Exits:**
• Forced exit at 15:45 if maximum days in trade exceeded
time_exit_details: Exit at **15:45** when maximum days in trade reached
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(152):** true
• Meaning: Always returns true
• Indicates: No filtering condition
• Trading use: Allows all breakout setups to pass

**PatternFast(153):** false (>152 case)
• Meaning: Always returns false
• Indicates: Never met condition
• Trading use: Used as negation filter (=false means condition passes)

**PatternFast(137):** (closed1 < opend1 and closed2 > opend2)
• Meaning: Yesterday red candle AND day before green candle
• Indicates: Mixed recent price action
• Trading use: Pattern filter for short entries (when false)
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Clear breakout logic with session-based levels
• Reasonable risk management (1:18 risk-reward ratio)
• Time-based position management prevents indefinite holding
• Multiple safety controls (max entries per day, max days in trade)

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Pattern filtering is essentially disabled (152=true, 153=false)
• Very wide profit target (900) vs small stop (50) may lead to low win rate
• No trend or momentum confirmation
• Session times may not align with optimal breakout periods
• Limited to 1 contract size

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Fixed stop loss at 50 currency units provides clear risk control
• Maximum 5 days in trade prevents extended drawdowns
• Daily entry limits control overtrading

**OVERALL:**
A **basic breakout system** with good risk controls but **minimal filtering**. The extreme risk-reward ratio suggests it's designed for high-probability setups, but the pattern filters don't provide meaningful selection criteria. Would benefit from **stronger momentum or trend confirmation** and more realistic profit targets.

tags: Trend Following Breakout with Pattern Filtering
summary: A **breakout strategy** that enters long positions at the next bar's high and short positions at the next bar's low, but only when specific pattern conditions are met. Uses **pattern filtering** with PatternFast(152) which always returns true, making this essentially an **unfiltered breakout system**.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• PatternFast(152) = true AND PatternFast(153) = false
• Buy next bar at high stop
• Within trading hours (08:00-22:00) excluding pause (12:00-11:00)
• Maximum 2 entries per day
• Long trades enabled and not restricted by day/month filters

**SHORT Entries:**
• PatternFast(152) = true AND PatternFast(153) = false
• Sell short next bar at low stop
• Same time and frequency restrictions as longs
• Short trades enabled and not restricted by day/month filters
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Exit on close when maximum days in trade reached (5 days)
• Forced exit at 21:45 (FlatTime) if max days exceeded

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 10 currency units
• Breakeven stop: 10 currency units
• Take profit: 650 currency units

**Time Exits:**
• Maximum 5 days in position
• Flat time at 21:45 when max days reached
time_exit_details: Exit at **21:45** when maximum days (5) in trade exceeded
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(152):** true
• Meaning: Always returns true (no filtering)
• Indicates: No pattern restriction
• Trading use: Allows all breakout entries

**PatternFast(153):** false (case >152)
• Meaning: Always returns false
• Indicates: Used as negative filter
• Trading use: Since it's negated (=false), this condition is always met

**Effective Pattern Logic:**
• PtnLY(152) AND NOT PtnLN(153) = true AND NOT false = true
• PtnSY(152) AND NOT PtnSN(153) = true AND NOT false = true
• Result: **No actual pattern filtering** - all breakouts are taken
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Clear breakout logic with stop entries
• Proper risk management with stop loss and take profit
• Position sizing control and daily entry limits
• Time-based exit prevents unlimited holding periods
• Session-based OHLC calculation for consistent breakout levels

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Pattern filtering is ineffective (always true conditions)
• Very tight stop loss (10) vs large profit target (650) creates poor risk/reward ratio
• Breakeven stop at same level as initial stop provides no benefit
• No trend or momentum filters - trades all breakouts regardless of market condition
• High profit target (650) may rarely be hit

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Stop loss: Extremely tight at 10 currency units
• Risk/reward ratio: 1:65 (unrealistic expectation)
• Position limits: Good daily and time-based controls

**OVERALL:**
This is essentially an **unfiltered breakout system** masquerading as a pattern-based strategy. The risk management is problematic with an unrealistic profit target that creates a poor win rate expectation. The strategy would benefit from **meaningful pattern filters** and **more realistic profit targets**.

tags: Session High/Low Breakout with Pattern Filters
summary: **Session breakout strategy** that enters long positions when price breaks above the highest high of the last 1-5 sessions, and short positions when price breaks below the lowest low. Uses **PatternFast filters** to validate entries and includes comprehensive time-based and calendar-based trade restrictions.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Price breaks above session high levels (next bar longLevel stop)
• Within trading window (07:00-14:00) excluding pause (12:00-11:00)
• LongEnabled = true
• Day of week ≠ NoLongDay (default 0)
• Month ≠ NoLongMonth (default 9 = September)
• PatternFast(PtnLY) = true AND PatternFast(PtnLN) = false
• Max 1 entry per day not exceeded
• LastTradeBar ≠ CurrentBar

**SHORT Entries:**
• Price breaks below session low levels (next bar shortLevel stop)
• Within trading window (07:00-14:00) excluding pause (12:00-11:00)
• ShortEnabled = false (disabled by default)
• Day of week ≠ NoShortDay (default 0)
• Month ≠ NoShortMonth (default 0)
• PatternFast(PtnSY) = true AND PatternFast(PtnSN) = false
• Max 1 entry per day not exceeded
• LastTradeBar ≠ CurrentBar
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Maximum 9 days in trade reached
• Flat at 15:55 if max days exceeded

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 60 currency units
• Take profit: 200 currency units
• Breakeven stop: disabled (0)

**Time Exits:**
• SetExitOnClose when max days in trade reached
• Forced exit at 15:55 (FlatTime) if position held too long
time_exit_details: Exit at **15:55** when max days in trade exceeded
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(PtnLY):** Default 152 = true
• Meaning: Always true condition
• Indicates: No pattern filter applied
• Trading use: Allow all long entries based on breakout

**PatternFast(PtnLN):** Default 153 = false
• Meaning: Always false condition
• Indicates: No negative pattern filter
• Trading use: No additional restriction on long entries

**PatternFast(PtnSY):** Default 152 = true
• Meaning: Always true condition
• Indicates: No pattern filter applied
• Trading use: Allow all short entries based on breakout

**PatternFast(PtnSN):** Default 153 = false
• Meaning: Always false condition
• Indicates: No negative pattern filter
• Trading use: No additional restriction on short entries
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Clean breakout logic with session-based levels
• Comprehensive risk management (stop loss, take profit, time exits)
• Flexible pattern filtering system for optimization
• Calendar-based filters (avoid certain days/months)
• Position tracking with days-in-trade counter
• Prevents multiple entries on same bar

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Short trading disabled by default (ShortEnabled = false)
• No long trades in September by default - questionable seasonal bias
• Pattern filters set to always true/false (no real filtering)
• Time window logic appears flawed (pause time end < start)
• No volatility or market condition filters
• Hard-coded session times may not suit all instruments

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Stop loss: 60 currency units (reasonable)
• Take profit: 200 currency units (3.33:1 reward-risk ratio)
• Maximum 9 days in trade prevents indefinite holding
• One contract trading keeps risk controlled

**OVERALL:**
**Solid breakout framework** with good risk management structure, but **pattern filters are effectively disabled** and some logic issues need addressing. The **seasonal restriction on longs** seems arbitrary and **short trading is disabled**, limiting the strategy's effectiveness. **Time window logic needs correction** for proper implementation.

tags: Multi-session high/low breakout with pattern filtering
summary: This is a **trend following breakout strategy** that enters long positions when price breaks above the highest high of the last **5 sessions**, but only when specific pattern conditions are met. The strategy uses **PatternFast(152)** (always true) for long entries and **PatternFast(46)** as a filter to avoid entries when certain conditions exist.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Price breaks above the **highest high** of the last 5 sessions (nSessions=1 to 5)
• PatternFast(152) = true (always enabled)
• PatternFast(46) = false (filter condition)
• Within trading hours (24:00 to 18:00) excluding pause (12:00 to 11:00)
• Maximum 2 entries per day
• Long trades enabled
• Not on restricted day/month

**SHORT Entries:**
• Price breaks below the **lowest low** of the last 5 sessions
• PatternFast(152) = true (always enabled) 
• PatternFast(153) = false (always false, so shorts disabled)
• Same time and frequency restrictions as longs
• Short trades disabled in this configuration
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Maximum 5 days in trade (MaxDaysInTrade)
• Flat at 16:45 if max days reached

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss at 110 currency units
• Take profit at 550 currency units
• No breakeven stop (set to 0)

**Time Exits:**
• Exit on close if maximum days in trade reached
• Forced flat at 16:45 (FlatTime)
time_exit_details: Exit at **16:45** if maximum days in trade reached
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(152):** true
• Meaning: Always returns true
• Indicates: No pattern filtering applied
• Trading use: Allows all breakout entries when other conditions met

**PatternFast(46):** ((opend0-lowd0)> ((opend1-lowd1)*3))
• Meaning: Current bar's lower shadow is more than 3x previous bar's lower shadow
• Indicates: Significant increase in downward rejection/buying pressure
• Trading use: Filter to avoid longs when there's strong buying pressure at lows

**PatternFast(153):** Not defined in switch statement, defaults to false
• Meaning: Always returns false
• Indicates: Pattern number exceeds maximum (152)
• Trading use: Effectively disables short entries since condition cannot be met
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Clear breakout logic based on multiple session highs/lows
• Reasonable risk management with both stop loss (110) and take profit (550)
• Good risk-reward ratio of approximately 1:5
• Time-based controls prevent overtrading
• Maximum days in trade prevents getting stuck in bad positions

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Short entries effectively disabled due to PatternFast(153) always being false
• PatternFast(152) provides no filtering, allowing all breakout attempts
• PatternFast(46) filter may be too restrictive and poorly understood
• No trending filter to avoid breakouts in choppy markets
• Single contract trading limits position sizing flexibility

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Stop loss of 110 currency units provides downside protection
• Take profit at 550 creates positive expectancy potential

tags: Pattern-filtered hourly bias system with time-based entries and exits
summary: This is a **bias strategy** that trades specific hours of the day based on **pattern filters**. It uses 60-minute bars and enters trades at predetermined hours (**MyLEbar** for longs, **MySEbar** for shorts) only when certain **PatternFast conditions** are met, with **time-based exits** at fixed hours.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• At hour **MyLEbar** (input parameter, default 14)
• **PatternFast(MyPtnLY)** must be TRUE (default pattern 26)
• **PatternFast(MyPtnLN)** must be FALSE (default pattern 37)
• Day of week cannot equal **MyNotLEDay** (default 3 = Wednesday)

**SHORT Entries:**
• At hour **MySEbar** (input parameter, default 10)
• **PatternFast(MyPtnSY)** must be TRUE (default pattern 5)
• **PatternFast(MyPtnSN)** must be FALSE (default pattern 44)
• Day of week cannot equal **MyNotSEDay** (default 5 = Friday)
exit_conditions:
**Time Exits:**
• LONG exits: At hour **MyLXbar** (default 8)
• SHORT exits: At hour **MySXbar** (default 21)

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss if **MyStop** > 0
• Take profit if **MyProfit** > 0
time_exit_details: Exits at **hour 8** for longs and **hour 21** for shorts based on session hour count
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(26):** body5d < 0.75 * range5d
• Meaning: 5-day body less than 75% of 5-day range
• Indicates: Moderate consolidation over 5 sessions
• Trading use: LONG entry filter (must be TRUE)

**PatternFast(5):** body1d > 0.25 * range1d
• Meaning: Yesterday's body greater than 25% of range
• Indicates: Decent momentum in previous session
• Trading use: SHORT entry filter (must be TRUE)

**PatternFast(37):** (highd0-opend0) > (highd1-opend1) * 2.5
• Meaning: Today's upper wick 2.5x larger than yesterday's
• Indicates: Strong rejection/exhaustion at highs
• Trading use: LONG entry filter (must be FALSE - no exhaustion)

**PatternFast(44):** (opend0-lowd0) > (opend1-lowd1) * 2
• Meaning: Today's lower wick 2x larger than yesterday's
• Indicates: Strong rejection/support at lows
• Trading use: SHORT entry filter (must be FALSE - no strong support)
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Well-structured **session-based logic** with proper OHLC handling
• **Pattern filtering** prevents entries during unfavorable conditions
• **Day-of-week filters** account for weekly market behavior
• **Test mode capability** for validating entry times
• **Fixed time exits** prevent overnight risk

**WEAKNESSES:**
• **No take profit** by default (MyProfit = 0)
• **Hardcoded time logic** may not adapt to changing market conditions
• **Limited pattern diversity** - only 4 basic patterns
• **No position sizing** based on volatility or risk
• **Session times** must be manually configured correctly

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• **120 currency unit** stop loss provides downside protection
• **Time-based exits** limit exposure duration
• **Day filters** avoid problematic trading days
• **Pattern filters** reduce poor entry timing

**OVERALL:**
This is a **solid bias framework** with good structural elements but **limited profit capture**. The pattern filtering is logical but basic. The **time-based approach** works well for **intraday bias strategies** but requires careful **session configuration** and **market-specific optimization**.

**PatternFast(152):** true

**PatternFast(102):** lowd0 > (lowd1 + lowd1*1*0.01)
• Meaning: Today's low > yesterday's low + 1%

The strategy would benefit from more sophisticated **market state filters** and dynamic exit conditions.

tags: Mean Reversion Bollinger Band Bounce

pattern_details:

tags: Channel Breakout with Pattern Filters
summary: A **trend following strategy** that uses **channel breakouts** (highest high/lowest low) with sophisticated **pattern filtering** for entries. The strategy trades both long and short, using **neutral and directional patterns** to confirm market conditions before executing breakout trades.

pattern_details:

• Indicates: Significant price movement over 5-day period

tags: Channel Breakout with Pattern Filtering
summary: This is a **trend following strategy** using **channel breakouts** with sophisticated **pattern filtering**. It trades both long and short based on breakouts of 1-bar high/low channels, but only when specific market patterns are present and absent.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Buy next bar at **upperchannel** (highest high of 1 bar) stop
• **PatternFast(64)** must be TRUE: highd0 < (lowd0 + lowd0*2*0.01) - indicating constrained daily range
• **PatternFast(116)** must be FALSE: NOT (opend0 < lowd1 OR opend0 > highd1) - current open must be within yesterday's range
• Within time window (18:00-17:00) excluding pause (12:00-11:00)
• Maximum 2 entries per day

**SHORT Entries:**
• Sell short next bar at **lowerchannel** (lowest low of 1 bar) stop
• **PatternFast(54)** must be TRUE: highd0 > (lowd0 + lowd0*0.5*0.01) - indicating minimum daily range expansion
• **PatternFast(50)** must be FALSE: NOT (closed1<closed2<closed3<closed4<closed5) - avoiding strong downtrends
• Same time and frequency restrictions as longs
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Maximum **5 days** in trade - forced exit at 16:45
• SetExitOnClose after max days reached

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: **280** in currency
• Take profit: **650** in currency
• Breakeven: **0** (disabled)

**Time Exits:**
• Flat time at **16:45** when max days reached
• No daily exit otherwise
time_exit_details: Exit at **16:45** when maximum days in trade reached
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(64):** highd0 < (lowd0 + lowd0*2*0.01)
• Meaning: Today's high is less than today's low plus 2% of low
• Indicates: Very constrained daily range, low volatility
• Trading use: Long entry filter for breakout setup

**PatternFast(116):** opend0 < lowd1 OR opend0 > highd1
• Meaning: Today's open is outside yesterday's range (gap)
• Indicates: Gap up or gap down scenario
• Trading use: Long entry filter (FALSE = no gap required)

**PatternFast(54):** highd0 > (lowd0 + lowd0*0.5*0.01)
• Meaning: Today's high exceeds low plus 0.5% of low
• Indicates: Minimum daily range expansion
• Trading use: Short entry filter for volatility

**PatternFast(50):** closed1<closed2<closed3<closed4<closed5
• Meaning: Five consecutive declining closes
• Indicates: Strong bearish momentum
• Trading use: Short entry filter (FALSE = avoid strong downtrends)
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• **Sophisticated pattern filtering** prevents trades in unfavorable conditions
• **Risk management** with both stop loss (280) and profit target (650)
• **Time controls** limit exposure with max 5 days in trade
• **Seasonal filters** can disable longs/shorts by day or month
• **Position sizing** control with contract specification

**WEAKNESSES:**
• **1-bar channel** is extremely sensitive and prone to whipsaws
• **Complex pattern logic** may create rare entry opportunities
• **Asymmetric pattern filters** (different for long/short) lack clear rationale
• **Currency-based stops** don't adapt to instrument volatility
• **No trailing stops** to protect profits in trends

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Stop loss at 280 currency units provides downside protection
• Maximum 5 days exposure limits time-based risk
• Daily entry limits prevent overtrading
• 1:2.32 risk/reward ratio (280 stop, 650 target) is reasonable

**OVERALL:**
This is a **sophisticated but potentially over-optimized** strategy. The pattern filtering shows advanced market understanding but may create too few trading opportunities. The **1-bar breakout** is extremely aggressive and likely to generate many false signals despite the filtering.

tags: Time-based Mean Reversion with ADX Filter
summary: A **time-specific reversal strategy** that trades mean reversion at 17:00 on 60-minute bars. Uses **ADX filter** (< 45) to avoid trending markets and employs **pattern-based entry conditions** with asymmetric long/short criteria.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Time = 17:00 (MyTime)
• ADX < 45 (low trend strength)
• PatternFast(5) = TRUE (body1d > 0.25 * range1d - moderate body size)
• PatternFast(49) = FALSE (NOT 4 consecutive higher closes)
• Day of week ≠ 5 (Friday excluded)
• Entry: Buy at Low - 0.1*Range (limit order below low)

**SHORT Entries:**
• Time = 17:00 (MyTime)
• ADX < 45 (low trend strength)
• PatternFast(57) = TRUE (highd0 > lowd0 + lowd0*1.5*0.01 - daily range > 1.5%)
• PatternFast(72) = FALSE (NOT closed1 < closed2-1% decline)
• Day of week ≠ 2 (Tuesday excluded)
• Entry: Sell at High + 0.1*Range (limit order above high)
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Exit on close (setexitonclose)
• Flat time at 15:00 (FlatTime)

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Profit target: 2250 in currency
• Breakeven: 1250 in currency
• Trailing stop: 30% retracement from max profit after 1500 trigger

**Time Exits:**
• Mandatory exit at 15:00
• Exit on close enabled
stop_loss_level: None - No fixed stop loss set
time_exit_details: Exit at **15:00** (FlatTime)
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(5):** body1d > 0.25 * range1d
• Meaning: Previous day's body is greater than 25% of its range
• Indicates: Moderate to strong directional movement
• Trading use: Confirms sufficient volatility for reversal

**PatternFast(57):** highd0 > (lowd0 + lowd0*2*0.01)
• Meaning: Today's high > today's low + 2% of low price
• Indicates: Minimum daily range of 2%
• Trading use: Volatility filter for short entries

**PatternFast(49):** closed1>closed2>closed3>closed4>closed5
• Meaning: Four consecutive higher closes
• Indicates: Strong upward momentum
• Trading use: Avoid longs when trend is too strong (reversal filter)

**PatternFast(72):** closed1 < (closed2 - closed2*1*0.01)
• Meaning: Yesterday's close < prior close minus 1%
• Indicates: Significant daily decline (1%+)
• Trading use: Avoid shorts after big down moves (reversal filter)
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• ADX filter prevents trading in strong trends
• Asymmetric day-of-week filters (different for long/short)
• Trailing stop mechanism preserves profits
• Time-based approach with specific reversal timing
• Breakeven protection reduces risk

**WEAKNESSES:**
• No fixed stop loss creates unlimited risk
• Single time entry (17:00) limits opportunities
• Complex pattern logic may overfit
• Limit orders may not fill in fast markets
• Max 1 entry per day severely limits activity

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Profit target and breakeven provide some protection
• Trailing stop helps preserve gains
• **MAJOR FLAW:** No stop loss means potential large losses
• Position sizing limited to single contract

**OVERALL:**
Interesting **mean reversion concept** with good trend avoidance, but **dangerous lack of stop loss** is a critical flaw. The **asymmetric filters** show sophistication, but the strategy needs proper risk controls to be viable.

tags: Algorithmic Trading System (ATS) with Bollinger Band Phases and Support/Resistance Clusters
summary: This is a sophisticated **multi-timeframe breakout strategy** that analyzes 6 timeframes (15min to Monthly) using **Bollinger Band phases** and **support/resistance clusters**. It enters positions on two main scenarios: **UC1** (expansion breakouts from P2H Bollinger phase) and **UC2** (signal-based entries from moving average crossovers). The system includes comprehensive **pattern filtering** and **multi-horizon risk management**.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• **UC1 Scenario:** Bollinger Band expansion (P2H phase) on UT1 or UT2 with valid duration filter
• **UC2 Scenario:** Moving average signals (XH, NXH, XPH) within recent distance
• **Pattern Filters:** Must pass PatternNeutralFast conditions and avoid negative directional patterns
• **Cluster Requirement:** Support cluster detected (3+ levels within param_ClusterPips)
• **Session Filter:** Within trading hours (0110-2200) avoiding pause periods
• **ADX Filter:** ADX(7) > 20 for trend strength
• **Multi-Horizon Check:** All daily/weekly/monthly profit limits respected

**SHORT Entries:**
• Currently disabled in this version (param_playShort capability exists but no short logic implemented)
exit_conditions:
**Partial Profit Taking:**
• Sell 50% at first resistance level when 2 contracts held
• Remaining contract targets second resistance level

**Trailing Stop:**
• SetTrailingStop_pt(60) = 60 points trailing stop on remaining position

**Scenario-Specific Exits:**
• UC1 trades exit on Bollinger contraction signals

**Profit Protection:**
• If MaxPositionProfit >= 6000 and current profit drops below 80% of max, exit immediately

**Time-Based Exits:**
• Close all positions on Friday if param_CloseOnFriday = 1
• Close at session end if param_ExitOnSessionClose = 1
• Maximum 5 days in trade limit
take_profit_level:
• Partial: First resistance level or close + **70 points**
• Final: SetTrailingStop_pt(**60**) = 60 **points** trailing stop
time_exit_details: Exit on **Friday close** and **session end** (2200), plus **5-day maximum trade duration**
function_patterns: PatternNeutralFast(12); PatternNeutralFast(55); PatternNeutralFast(46); PatternNeutralFast(56); PatternDirectionalFast(52); PatternDirectionalFast(35); PatternNeutralFast(53); PatternDirectionalFast(16); ADX(7)
pattern_details:
**PatternNeutralFast(12):** body5d < 0.75 * (highd5-lowd1)
• Meaning: 5-day body less than 75% of 5-day range from high to low
• Indicates: Moderate consolidation pattern
• Trading use: Allows entries during controlled volatility

**PatternNeutralFast(55):** (highd0>(lowd0+lowd0*1*0.01))
• Meaning: Current high exceeds low plus 1% of low value
• Indicates: Minimum daily range requirement
• Trading use: Ensures adequate volatility for trade

**PatternNeutralFast(46):** ((opend0-lowd0)> ((opend1-lowd1)*3))
• Meaning: Current open-to-low distance exceeds 3x previous period
• Indicates: Significant gap or volatility expansion
• Trading use: Filters for strong momentum moves

**PatternDirectionalFast(52):** highd1<highd2 and lowd1<lowd2
• Meaning: Previous bar's high and low both below prior bar
• Indicates: Inside bar pattern (consolidation)
• Trading use: Filters for breakout setups after consolidation

**PatternDirectionalFast(35):** ((highd0-opend0)> ((highd1-opend1)*1.5))
• Meaning: Current high-open distance exceeds 1.5x previous period
• Indicates: Strong upward momentum within bar
• Trading use: Confirms bullish intrabar action
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• **Multi-timeframe analysis** across 6 timeframes provides comprehensive market view
• **Sophisticated risk management** with daily/weekly/monthly profit limits and drawdown controls
• **Support/resistance cluster detection** improves entry timing and reduces false signals
• **Bollinger Band phase analysis** helps identify optimal market conditions for breakouts
• **Pattern filtering system** with 150+ patterns reduces poor-quality setups
• **Partial profit taking** and trailing stops optimize trade management
• **Session filtering** avoids low-liquidity periods

**WEAKNESSES:**
• **Extremely complex code** with high computational overhead and potential for bugs
• **Over-optimization risk** with numerous parameters that may not work in different market conditions
• **No short trading** in current implementation limits profit opportunities
• **Hardcoded timeframe assumptions** may not adapt well to different instruments
• **Pattern logic complexity** makes it difficult to understand why trades are taken or rejected
• **Multiple exit conditions** could conflict and create unexpected behavior

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• **Excellent multi-horizon controls** prevent catastrophic losses across different time periods
• **Reasonable stop loss** at 100 points with trailing mechanism
• **Position sizing** with 2-contract partial profit approach
• **Maximum trade duration** prevents extended drawdowns
• **Profit protection mechanism** locks in gains when significant profits achieved

**OVERALL:**
This is a **highly sophisticated institutional-grade strategy** with excellent risk management but **excessive complexity**. The multi-timeframe approach and comprehensive filtering show advanced understanding, but the system may be **over-engineered** and difficult to maintain. The **missing short side** and complex pattern interactions could limit performance. Best suited for **experienced algorithmic traders** with significant computational resources and thorough backtesting capabilities.

tags: Multi-session range breakout with pattern filtering
summary: **EasterGold** is a sophisticated breakout strategy that trades above/below multi-session highs/lows. It uses **session-based OHLC calculation**, **ADX filtering**, and **multiple pattern confirmations** to enter breakout trades with comprehensive risk management including ATR-based stops.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Time window: 02:00-13:15 (excluding 12:00-11:00 pause)
• Buy at highest high of last 4 sessions (stop order)
• ADX < 85 (trend strength filter)
• PatternNeutralFast(32) AND PatternNeutralFast(55) = TRUE
• PatternNeutralFast(38) = FALSE
• PatternDirectionalFast(+21) = TRUE
• PatternDirectionalFast(-43) = FALSE
• Skip session 2 (Tuesday)

**SHORT Entries:**
• Same time and pattern conditions as long
• Sell short at lowest low of last 4 sessions (stop order)
• Skip session 0 (Sunday)
• PatternDirectionalFast uses negative values for short bias
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Exit on close if max days in trade reached
• Friday exit for longs at 23:00
• Tuesday exit for shorts at 09:00
• Spike profit exits (1% for longs, 0.6% for shorts)

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• ATR-based stops: 50 ATR for longs, 10 ATR for shorts (capped at 3000 currency)
• ATR-based targets: 13 ATR for longs, 12 ATR for shorts
• ATR-based breakeven: 6 ATR for longs, 0 ATR for shorts

**Time Exits:**
• Flat at 16:30 if position held beyond max days
• Day-of-week specific exits (Friday longs, Tuesday shorts)
stop_loss_level:
• **Primary:** ATR-based - SetStopLoss(stopATR * ATR * BigPointValue) in **currency**
• **Long positions:** 50 ATR periods, capped at **3000 currency** maximum
• **Short positions:** 10 ATR periods, capped at **3000 currency** maximum
• **Fallback:** SetStopLoss(**3000**) = 3000 in **currency**
take_profit_level:
• **ATR-based targets:**
• **Long positions:** SetProfitTarget(13 * ATR * BigPointValue) in **currency**
• **Short positions:** SetProfitTarget(12 * ATR * BigPointValue) in **currency**
• **Fallback:** SetProfitTarget(**4100**) = 4100 in **currency**
time_exit_details: Exit at **16:30** if max days reached, **Friday 23:00** for longs, **Tuesday 09:00** for shorts
function_patterns: PatternNeutralFast(32); PatternNeutralFast(55); PatternNeutralFast(38); PatternDirectionalFast(21); PatternDirectionalFast(-43); ADX(5)
pattern_details:
**PatternNeutralFast(32):** ((highd0-opend0)> ((highd1-opend1)*0.5))
• Meaning: Current session's upper wick > 50% of previous session's upper wick
• Indicates: Increased upward volatility
• Trading use: Breakout preparation signal

**PatternNeutralFast(55):** ((highd0>(lowd0+lowd0*1*0.01)))
• Meaning: Current high > current low + 1% of low
• Indicates: Minimum daily range requirement
• Trading use: Volatility filter

**PatternNeutralFast(38):** ((highd0-opend0)> ((highd1-opend1)*3))
• Meaning: Current upper wick > 3x previous upper wick
• Indicates: Excessive gap or volatility spike
• Trading use: Filter out abnormal conditions (used as FALSE)

**PatternDirectionalFast(21):** body5d > 2 * (highd5-lowd1)
• Meaning: 5-day body > 2x the range from 5 sessions ago high to yesterday's low
• Indicates: Strong directional move over 5 days
• Trading use: Trend confirmation for breakout direction

**PatternDirectionalFast(-43):** ((opend0-lowd0)> ((opend1-lowd1)*1.5))
• Meaning: Current lower wick > 1.5x previous lower wick
• Indicates: Strong downward rejection
• Trading use: Filter out conflicting signals (used as FALSE)
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• **Multi-session breakout logic** provides robust entry levels
• **Comprehensive pattern filtering** reduces false breakouts
• **ADX filter** avoids trades in choppy markets
• **ATR-based risk management** adapts to market volatility
• **Maximum stop loss cap** prevents catastrophic losses
• **Day-of-week filtering** accounts for market seasonality
• **Multiple exit strategies** including time, bias, and spike exits

**WEAKNESSES:**
• **Extremely complex** with 6+ pattern conditions making optimization difficult
• **Over-fitted appearance** with very specific pattern combinations
• **Asymmetric parameters** (different ATR values for long/short) may lack robustness
• **Multiple time filters** could significantly reduce trading frequency
• **Session calculation complexity** increases computational overhead

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• **Excellent stop loss protection** with ATR adaptation and hard caps
• **Position sizing** controlled via mycontracts input
• **Maximum days in trade** prevents indefinite exposure
• **Breakeven functionality** protects profits

**OVERALL:**
This is a **highly sophisticated breakout strategy** with excellent risk management but potentially **over-optimized complexity**. The multi-session range calculation and pattern filtering show advanced development, but the numerous conditions may reduce robustness. **Best suited for experienced traders** who can manage the complexity and parameter sensitivity.

tags: Time-based Mean Reversion with ADX Filter
summary: A **time-specific reversal strategy** that trades against momentum at 17:00 when ADX is below 45. Uses **pattern recognition** to identify setup conditions and applies comprehensive **position management** with trailing stops.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Time = 17:00 (1700)
• ADX < 45 (low trend strength)
• PatternFast(5) = TRUE (body1d > 0.25 * range1d - larger candle body)
• PatternFast(49) = FALSE (NOT 4 consecutive lower closes)
• Day of week ≠ 5 (Friday)
• Entry: Buy at Low - 0.1*Range (limit order below current low)

**SHORT Entries:**
• Time = 17:00 (1700)
• ADX < 45 (low trend strength)
• PatternFast(57) = TRUE (highd0 > lowd0 + lowd0*1.5*0.01 - minimum range requirement)
• PatternFast(72) = FALSE (NOT closed1 < closed2-closed2*1*0.01 - avoid strong down moves)
• Day of week ≠ 2 (Tuesday)
• Entry: Sell at High + 0.1*Range (limit order above current high)
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Exit on close enabled
• Flat time at 15:00 (1500)

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Profit target: 2250 in currency
• Breakeven: 1250 in currency
• Trailing stop when profit ≥ 1500

**Time Exits:**
• Mandatory exit at 15:00 next day
• End of session close
stop_loss_level: None - No fixed stop loss set
time_exit_details: Exit at **15:00** (FlatTime)
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(5):** body1d > 0.25 * range1d
• Meaning: Current bar body > 25% of its range
• Indicates: Decent sized move, not a doji
• Trading use: Ensures meaningful price action for long entry

**PatternFast(57):** highd0 > (lowd0 + lowd0*1.5*0.01)
• Meaning: Current high > low + 1.5% of low value
• Indicates: Minimum range requirement
• Trading use: Ensures sufficient volatility for short entry

**PatternFast(49):** closed1>closed2>closed3>closed4>closed5
• Meaning: Four consecutive higher closes
• Indicates: Strong upward momentum
• Trading use: Avoid longs when this is TRUE (countertrend)

**PatternFast(72):** closed1 < (closed2-closed2*1*0.01)
• Meaning: Close significantly below previous close (1%)
• Indicates: Strong downward move
• Trading use: Avoid shorts when this is TRUE (countertrend)
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Well-defined time-based approach with specific entry window
• ADX filter prevents trading in strong trending conditions
• Comprehensive position management with breakeven and trailing stops
• Pattern filters avoid trading in opposite momentum
• Day-of-week filters optimize performance
• Limit orders provide better fills

**WEAKNESSES:**
• No fixed stop loss creates unlimited risk potential
• Single time entry may miss other opportunities
• Reliance on specific patterns may reduce trade frequency
• 60-minute bars may be too slow for intraday reversals

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Breakeven protection at 1250 currency units
• Trailing stop system with 30% retrace from peak
• Daily position limits (MaxEntriesPerDay=1)
• Mandatory time exit prevents overnight exposure

**OVERALL:**
Well-structured **reversal strategy** with good risk controls. The **ADX filter** and **pattern recognition** show sophisticated market understanding. Main concern is **lack of fixed stop loss**, but trailing system and breakeven help mitigate risk.

tags: Session-based multi-timeframe breakout with pattern filtering
summary: A **breakout strategy** that trades breaks above/below session highs/lows from **N sessions ago** (default 3). Uses **dual pattern filtering** (one pattern must be true, another must be false) combined with **SMA trend filter** and **ADX volatility filter** to qualify entries.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• PatternFast(PtnLY=153) = TRUE and PatternFast(PtnLN=153) = FALSE
• Current close > SMA(50)
• ADX < 66 (low trending conditions)
• Break above high from 3 sessions ago
• Within trading window (08:00-14:00) excluding pause (11:00-12:00)
• Max 1 entry per day

**SHORT Entries:**
• PatternFast(PtnSY=81) = TRUE and PatternFast(PtnSN=23) = FALSE
• Current close < SMA(50)
• ADX < 66 (low trending conditions)
• Break below low from 3 sessions ago
• Within trading window (08:00-14:00) excluding pause (11:00-12:00)
• Max 1 entry per day
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Market orders at session end (intraweek/intraday based on TypeIntra setting)

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 1550 currency units
• Take profit: 4100 currency units
• Breakeven: Disabled (0)
• Trailing stop: 2000 trigger with 50% distance from runup

**Time Exits:**
• Intraweek: Exit Friday at session end
• Intraday: Exit daily at session end
time_exit_details: Exit based on **TypeIntra** setting - either daily or weekly session close
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(153):** Pattern > 152 = FALSE
• Meaning: Always returns false (disabled pattern)
• Indicates: No pattern requirement
• Trading use: Effectively removes pattern filter

**PatternFast(81):** highd0 > highd1
• Meaning: Current session high exceeds previous session high
• Indicates: Upward price momentum
• Trading use: Bullish breakout confirmation

**PatternFast(23):** body5d < 0.1 * range5d
• Meaning: 5-day body less than 10% of 5-day range
• Indicates: Extreme consolidation/low volatility
• Trading use: Coiled spring setup for breakout
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Multi-layered filtering (patterns, SMA, ADX)
• Session-based breakout levels provide clear entry points
• Risk management with stops, targets, and trailing
• Time-based position management prevents overnight risk
• Daily entry limits control overtrading

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Default pattern 153 is disabled (always false), removing key filter
• High profit target (4100) vs stop (1550) creates poor risk/reward of 1:2.6
• ADX < 66 filter may miss strong trending moves
• No position sizing based on volatility
• Trailing stop parameters may be too aggressive

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Fixed stop loss and profit target provide defined risk
• Trailing stop can lock in profits on favorable moves
• Time exits prevent overnight gaps
• Entry limits control daily exposure

**OVERALL:**
Solid **breakout framework** with good risk controls, but **pattern configuration appears suboptimal** with disabled filters. The strategy would benefit from **proper pattern optimization** and **better risk/reward ratios**. The multi-session lookback approach is innovative but needs **backtesting validation**.

tags: Session-based breakout with pattern filtering and ADX momentum filter
summary: This is a **bidirectional breakout strategy** that trades NQ futures using session-based high/low levels from N sessions ago. It combines **pattern recognition filters**, **ADX momentum filtering**, and **SMA bias confirmation** to enter breakouts above resistance or below support levels.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Time window: 8:00-14:00 (excluding 12:00-11:00 pause)
• PatternFast(PtnLY) = TRUE AND PatternFast(PtnLN) = FALSE
• Current close > SMA(50)
• ADX < 66 (low momentum filter)
• Max 1 entry per day
• Buy stop at high of N sessions ago

**SHORT Entries:**
• Same time window and day limits
• PatternFast(PtnSY) = TRUE AND PatternFast(PtnSN) = FALSE
• Current close < SMA(50)
• ADX < 66 (low momentum filter)
• Sell short stop at low of N sessions ago
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Trailing stop when enabled: 50% retracement from runup after 2000 profit trigger

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 1550 in currency
• Take profit: 4100 in currency
• Breakeven: Disabled (0)

**Time Exits:**
• Intraweek mode: Exit Friday between session end -40 to session end +20
• Intraday mode: Exit daily between session end -40 to session end +20
time_exit_details: Exit at **session end -40 minutes** to **session end +20 minutes** based on TypeIntra setting
function_patterns: PatternFast(PtnLY); PatternFast(PtnLN); PatternFast(PtnSY); PatternFast(PtnSN); ADX; SMA
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(81):** (highd0>(highd1))
• Meaning: Current session high > previous session high
• Indicates: Upward breakout momentum
• Trading use: Bullish breakout confirmation

**PatternFast(23):** body5d < 0.1 * range5d
• Meaning: 5-session body less than 10% of 5-session range
• Indicates: Extreme consolidation, very low volatility
• Trading use: Breakout setup after compression

**ADX Filter:** ADX < 66
• Meaning: Average Directional Index below threshold
• Indicates: Low to moderate trending conditions
• Trading use: Avoid high momentum false breakouts

**SMA Bias:** Close vs SMA(50)
• Meaning: Price relative to 50-period moving average
• Indicates: Market bias direction
• Trading use: Long only above SMA, short only below SMA
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Solid breakout framework with session-based levels
• Multiple confirmation filters reduce false signals
• ADX filter prevents trading in overly trending markets
• SMA bias filter aligns trades with market direction
• Proper risk management with stops and targets
• Time-based exits prevent overnight exposure
• Trailing stop captures extended moves

**WEAKNESSES:**
• High stop loss (1550) vs profit target (4100) creates unfavorable 1:2.6 ratio
• Complex pattern combinations may over-optimize
• Limited to 1 trade per day may miss opportunities
• Session-based levels may not adapt to intraday volatility
• ADX threshold at 66 is quite restrictive

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Fixed stop loss provides consistent risk control
• Position sizing limited to specified contracts
• Daily trade limits prevent overtrading
• Time exits eliminate gap risk

**OVERALL:**
Well-structured breakout strategy with **comprehensive filtering system**. The combination of pattern recognition, momentum filtering, and bias confirmation creates a **robust entry framework**. However, the **risk-reward ratio** and restrictive filters may limit profitability. Best suited for **range-bound to moderately trending markets**.

tags: Bollinger Band Mean Reversion
summary: A **mean reversion strategy** that enters positions when price crosses back into the Bollinger Bands after touching the extremes, combined with specific pattern conditions. Trades the expectation that price will revert to the mean after extreme moves.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• PatternFast(66) = true (current low > previous low by 3%+)
• PatternFast(1) = false (body NOT less than 10% of range)
• Price crosses over lower Bollinger Band
• Within trading hours (15:00-20:00) excluding pause (11:00-12:00)
• Max 1 entry per day

**SHORT Entries:**
• PatternFast(102) = true (current low > previous low by 1%+)
• PatternFast(94) = false (5-day high NOT less than current high)
• Price crosses under upper Bollinger Band
• Same time and frequency restrictions
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Stop loss, breakeven, or profit target hit
• Trailing stop if enabled

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 1000 currency units
• Breakeven: 2500 currency units
• Profit target: 7000 currency units

**Time Exits:**
• Maximum 4 days in trade
• Flat at 15:00 if max days reached
• Exit on close when time limits hit
time_exit_details: Exit at **15:00** if maximum 4 days in trade reached
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(66):** lowd0<(lowd1+lowd1*3*0.01)
• Meaning: Current low is below previous low plus 3%
• Indicates: Significant downward price movement
• Trading use: Oversold condition for long entry

**PatternFast(1):** body1d < 0.1 * range1d
• Meaning: Yesterday's body less than 10% of range

pattern_details:
**PatternNeutralFast(4):** Corresponds to PatternFast(4)

quality_analysis:

tags: Asymmetric Long/Short bias with Donchian breakouts
summary: A **day-of-week bias strategy** that trades crude oil (@CL) on 15-minute bars. Goes **long only on Thursdays** (sow=5) with Donchian breakouts and **short only on Sundays** (sow=1) with Donchian breakdowns, using different time windows for each direction.
entry_conditions:

• Day of week = 1 (Sunday)

• Low <= lowest close over 4 periods (Donchian breakdown)

pattern_details:
**PatternFast(152):** true
• Meaning: Always returns true condition
• Indicates: No pattern filtering for long trades
• Trading use: Allows all qualifying long setups

**PatternFast(14):** body5d < 1.5 * (highd5-lowd1)
• Meaning: 5-day body less than 1.5x the range from 5-day high to 1-day low
• Indicates: Moderate consolidation pattern
• Trading use: Filters for ranging/consolidating markets before short breakdowns

**Donchian Channel:** highest(c,2) for longs, lowest(c,4) for shorts
• Meaning: Breakout above 2-period high close (long) or breakdown below 4-period low close (short)
• Indicates: Short-term momentum breakouts/breakdowns
• Trading use: Entry trigger for directional moves

**WEAKNESSES:**

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Fixed stop loss at 1.5 points provides downside protection
• Take profit at 3 points gives 2:1 reward/risk
• Time exits prevent overnight exposure
• SetStopContract limits risk per position

**OVERALL:**
**Mediocre strategy** with interesting bias concept but **poor execution**. The day-of-week restriction severely limits opportunities, and the **asymmetric design lacks coherent logic**. The long side has no real pattern filtering while shorts use a moderate filter. **Risk management is adequate** but the overall approach seems more like curve-fitting than robust market behavior.

**SHORT Entries:**

pattern_details:

**WEAKNESSES:**

tags: Session-based intraday breakout with gap confirmation
summary: This strategy trades **session breakouts** when today's opening gaps relative to yesterday's close, combined with **directional confirmation** from the previous day's close-to-open relationship. It uses **trailing stops** and **time-based risk management** for position control.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Today's session high (highd0) > yesterday's close (closed2)
• Yesterday opened above its close (opend1 > closed1)
• Within trading window (8:30-12:00, excluding pause 12:00-11:00)
• Weekday filter excludes Friday
• Max 1 entry per day

**SHORT Entries:**
• Today's session low (lowd0) < yesterday's close (closed2)
• Yesterday opened below its close (opend1 < closed1)
• Same time and risk filters as long
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Maximum 7 days in trade
• Flat at 25:00 (next day 1:00 AM) if max days reached

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 650 currency units
• No profit target set

**Trailing Stop:**
• Activates when profit ≥ 1300 currency units
• Trails at 60% of maximum runup from entry
• Only after holding > 1 bar
time_exit_details: Exit at **01:00** (FlatTime=2500) when maximum days in trade reached
pattern_details:
**_ohlcmulti5 Function:**
• Purpose: Calculates session-based OHLC for current and past 5 sessions
• Returns: Array with current session and historical session data
• Usage: Provides highd0, lowd0, opend1, closed1, closed2 values
• Trading use: Session breakout detection and gap analysis

**Gap Pattern Logic:**
• Combines current session breakout with previous session gap direction
• Long when today breaks above yesterday's close AND yesterday gapped up
• Short when today breaks below yesterday's close AND yesterday gapped down
• Confirms directional bias with gap follow-through
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Solid session-based breakout logic with gap confirmation
• Good risk management with trailing stops and time exits
• Reasonable position sizing controls (max entries per day)
• Combines multiple timeframe perspectives (current vs previous session)

**WEAKNESSES:**
• No profit target could lead to giving back gains
• Relatively large stop loss (650) without corresponding profit target
• Simple gap logic may not account for different gap sizes
• Friday filter seems arbitrary without clear rationale

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Fixed stop loss provides downside protection
• Trailing stop preserves profits once threshold reached
• Time-based exits prevent indefinite holding
• Daily entry limits control overexposure

**OVERALL:**
Well-structured **intraday breakout strategy** with good risk controls. The combination of **gap analysis** and **session breakouts** provides logical entry criteria. However, the lack of profit targets and relatively large stops may impact risk-reward ratios. The **trailing stop mechanism** is sophisticated and helps preserve gains.

pattern_details:

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**

tags: Session-based Pattern Breakout with ADX Filter

pattern_details:
**PatternFast(152):** PatternFast = true
• Meaning: Always returns true
• Indicates: No pattern restriction
• Trading use: Default 'always enter' condition

**PatternFast(47):** closed1>closed2 and closed2>closed3 and closed3>closed4
• Meaning: Three consecutive higher closes
• Indicates: Strong upward momentum
• Trading use: Bullish trend confirmation (strategy uses as FALSE condition)

**PatternFast(5):** body1d > 0.25 * range1d
• Meaning: Previous day's body > 25% of its range
• Indicates: Strong directional movement, not a doji
• Trading use: Confirms meaningful price action

**PatternFast(153):** case >152: PatternFast = false
• Meaning: Always returns false
• Indicates: Pattern exclusion
• Trading use: Default 'never restrict' condition

**ADX Filter:** ADX < 100 (effectively always true)
• Meaning: Trend strength below maximum threshold
• Indicates: No strong trending condition restriction
• Trading use: Minimal filter, allows most market conditions

**WEAKNESSES:**

• No take profit creates unlimited risk exposure
• Time exit at 2:00 AM is unusual and may hit during low liquidity

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Stop loss is too large relative to entry precision
• No position sizing relative to account equity
• Missing take profit creates asymmetric risk profile

**OVERALL:**
This strategy has a **solid session framework** but suffers from **poor pattern implementation** and **inadequate risk management**. The concept of breakout trading around specific times is sound, but the execution needs significant refinement. The **pattern conditions are essentially meaningless** in their current form, and the **risk/reward ratio is heavily skewed against profitability**.

**PatternFast(81):** highd0 > highd1

**PatternFast(129):** range1d < (highd2-lowd2) and (highd2-lowd2) < (highd3-lowd3)

quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**

**WEAKNESSES:**

tags: Multi-day session breakout with pattern filters
summary: This is a **multi-day breakout strategy** for NQ futures trading 5-minute bars during extended sessions (17:00-16:00). It uses **session-based OHLC levels** from previous days as breakout triggers, with pattern filters to refine entry timing and multi-day holding capability.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Price breaks below previous day's low (l <= ELL)
• Pattern filter: Close near low of range ((closed1-lowd1)<0.50*(highd1-lowd1))
• NOT PtnLN: Previous close NOT significantly above 2 days ago
• Within time window and not skip day

**SHORT Entries:**
• Price breaks above previous day's high (h >= ELS)
• Pattern filter: Close well above open (closed1>(opend1+opend1*1.50/100))
• Within time window and not skip day
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Manual stop loss at 85 points via calculation
• Manual take profit at 130 points via calculation
• Breakeven exit when profit >= 100 points

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• SetProfitTarget(SpikeProfit * bigpointvalue) = 135 in **currency**

**Time Exits:**
• Max holding: 9 days for longs, 3 days for shorts
• Force exit at 15:55-16:00 on max day
• Force exit next day if beyond max days
stop_loss_level:
• Manual calculation: **85 points** (SL * bigpointvalue)
• Also uses SetProfitTarget as spike protection
take_profit_level:
• Manual calculation: **130 points** (TP * bigpointvalue)
• SetProfitTarget(**135**) = 135 in **currency** (spike protection)
time_exit_details: Exit at **15:55-16:00** on max holding day, or immediately if beyond max days
pattern_details:
**PtnLY:** ((closed1-lowd1)<0.50*(highd1-lowd1))
• Meaning: Yesterday's close in lower 50% of the day's range
• Indicates: Weak close, potential downside continuation
• Trading use: Long entry filter (bearish setup)

**PtnLN:** ((closed1>(closed2+closed2*0.50/100)))
• Meaning: Yesterday's close 0.5% above close from 2 days ago
• Indicates: Upward momentum from 2 days ago
• Trading use: Used as negative filter for longs (avoid when true)

**PtnSY:** (closed1>(opend1+opend1*1.50/100))
• Meaning: Yesterday's close 1.5% above yesterday's open
• Indicates: Strong bullish daily performance
• Trading use: Short entry filter (countertrend short after strength)

**_OHLCMulti5Rev2:** Session OHLC calculator
• Meaning: Calculates session-based OHLC values for multiple days
• Indicates: Provides breakout levels (previous day high/low)
• Trading use: Core breakout level calculation
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Multi-day holding allows capturing larger moves
• Session-based OHLC calculation provides clean breakout levels
• Pattern filters add discretion to raw breakouts
• Asymmetric holding periods (9 vs 3 days) shows market understanding
• Breakeven protection preserves profits

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Counterintuitive logic: longs on downside breaks, shorts on upside breaks
• Pattern filters seem arbitrary (0.5% vs 1.5% thresholds)
• Mixed exit methods create complexity (manual + SetProfitTarget)
• No volume or volatility filters
• Skip day logic unclear

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Reasonable 85-point stop loss for NQ
• 130-point profit target (1.53:1 reward/risk)
• Multi-day time stops prevent indefinite holding
• One-direction-per-session prevents overtrading

**OVERALL:**
This appears to be a **mean reversion strategy** disguised as breakout logic. The counterintuitive entries (long on breaks down, short on breaks up) suggest it's fading breakouts rather than following them. The **multi-day holding** is interesting but the **pattern logic needs clarification** for practical implementation.

tags: ATR-based Opening Range Breakout with Pattern Filtering
summary: This is an **Opening Range Breakout (ORB)** strategy for **@FDAX** that uses **ATR bands** around the session opening price to trigger long/short entries. The strategy employs **multiple pattern filters** to validate entries and includes comprehensive **risk management** with stop loss, take profit, and breakeven settings.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Price breaks above **opend0 + (ATR * 2.0)** on stop order
• Time window: **10:00 to 21:00**
• PatternNeutralFast(26) = TRUE (neutral pattern required)
• PatternNeutralFast(56) = FALSE (specific pattern excluded)
• PatternFast(51) = TRUE (long pattern confirmation)
• PatternFast(153) = FALSE (long pattern exclusion)
• Skip trading on day of week = 4 (Thursday)

**SHORT Entries:**
• Price breaks below **opend0 - (ATR * 2.0)** on stop order
• Same time window and neutral pattern requirements
• PatternFast(51) = TRUE (short pattern confirmation)
• PatternFast(153) = FALSE (short pattern exclusion)
• Skip trading on day of week = 1 (Monday)
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Maximum days in trade: **10 days**
• Exit on close if max days reached
• Forced exit at **21:30** if max days condition met

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: **90 points** (currency-based)
• Take profit: **420 points** (currency-based)
• Breakeven: **240 points** (currency-based)

**Time Exits:**
• Flat time at **21:30** when max days condition is active
time_exit_details: Exit at **21:30** when maximum days in trade condition is met
pattern_details:
**PatternNeutralFast(26):** body5d < 0.75 * range5d
• Meaning: 5-day body less than 75% of 5-day range
• Indicates: Moderate consolidation pattern
• Trading use: Neutral market condition filter

**PatternNeutralFast(56):** highd0>(lowd0+lowd0*1.5*0.01)
• Meaning: Today's high > today's low + 1.5% of today's low
• Indicates: Minimum daily range requirement
• Trading use: Volatility filter (excluded when true)

**PatternFast(51):** highd1>highd2 and lowd1>lowd2
• Meaning: Yesterday's high > day before high AND yesterday's low > day before low
• Indicates: Inside bar pattern (higher lows and higher highs)
• Trading use: Trend continuation setup

**PatternFast(153):** Always FALSE (pattern > 152)
• Meaning: Invalid pattern number, always returns false
• Indicates: Placeholder or error in pattern selection
• Trading use: Effectively no additional filter
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Well-structured **ATR-based breakout** system with dynamic levels
• Good **risk management** with stop loss (90), take profit (420), and breakeven (240)
• **Day-of-week filters** to avoid unfavorable market conditions
• **Maximum holding period** (10 days) prevents extended losses
• Uses session-based OHLC calculation for accurate entry levels

**WEAKNESSES:**
• **Pattern 153 is invalid** (always false) - suggests configuration error
• **Asymmetric day filters** (skip Thursday for longs, Monday for shorts) lacks clear rationale
• **No volume or volatility confirmation** beyond basic ATR
• **Large stop-to-target ratio** (1:4.67) may result in low win rate
• **Pattern logic complexity** makes optimization and maintenance difficult

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• **Adequate position sizing** with contract specification
• **Multi-layered exits** with stop, target, and breakeven
• **Time-based risk control** with maximum days in trade
• **Currency-based stops** provide consistent risk per trade

**OVERALL:**
This is a **moderately sophisticated breakout strategy** with good risk management framework, but suffers from **pattern configuration issues** and **overly complex filtering**. The core ORB concept is sound, but the execution could be simplified for better reliability and maintainability.

tags: Compression Breakout with Body Trigger
summary: A **compression breakout strategy** that enters long/short positions after price compression periods when a strong body trigger occurs. Uses **different parameters for long vs short** setups and requires price to be on opposite side of moving average from intended direction.
entry_conditions:

• ADX < 60
• Within trading hours (9:00-21:00, pause 13:00-14:00)

**SHORT Entries:**
• Price compression in last 50 bars < 6% of average close
• Current bar body > 3.4x average body of last 50 bars (bearish body)
• Close < 20-period MA
• PatternFast(100) = true AND PatternFast(50) = false
• ADX < 60
• Within trading hours (9:00-21:00, pause 13:00-14:00)
• Max 2 entries per day
exit_conditions:

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Long: Stop loss and profit target
• Short: Stop loss and profit target
• Breakeven stop available

**Time Exits:**
• Maximum days in trade limit
• Flat at specific time if max days reached
time_exit_details: Exit after **4 days maximum** in trade, executed at **20:00** or later
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(152):** true
• Meaning: Always true condition
• Indicates: No pattern restriction
• Trading use: Allows entry when other conditions met

**PatternFast(150):** C < opend0*0.995
• Meaning: Current close < 99.5% of current open
• Indicates: Bearish intraday action

**PatternFast(100):** lowd0 > lowd1

**PatternFast(50):** closed1<closed2<closed3<closed4<closed5

• Indicates: Strong downward momentum

quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• **Dual-timeframe approach** with different parameters for long/short
• **Price compression filter** identifies low volatility before breakouts
• **Body trigger mechanism** confirms momentum
• **ADX filter** avoids overly trending markets
• **Risk management** with stops, targets, and breakeven
• **Time-based exits** prevent extended drawdowns

**WEAKNESSES:**
• **Asymmetric logic** makes it complex and hard to optimize
• **Pattern combination** (152 AND NOT 150) seems arbitrary
• **Different compression thresholds** (8% vs 6%) lack clear justification
• **Moving average conflict** - enters long above MA but compression suggests ranging market
• **High stop losses** relative to typical intraday moves

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• **Good position sizing** with contract control
• **Reasonable stop losses** but quite wide for intraday
• **Profit targets** well-defined with asymmetric risk/reward
• **Maximum days limit** prevents extended exposure

**OVERALL:**
**Sophisticated breakout system** with solid risk management but **overly complex parameter structure**. The asymmetric long/short logic makes it **difficult to validate and optimize**. Would benefit from **simplified, symmetric approach** while maintaining core compression breakout concept.

tags: Session-based multi-pattern filtered breakout with ADX confirmation
summary: This is a **sophisticated intraday breakout strategy** that trades breakouts above session highs (long) or below session lows (short). It uses **multiple pattern filters, ADX confirmation**, and **asymmetric stops/targets** for long vs short positions.
