function_patterns: PatternFast(MyPtnLY); PatternFast(MyPtnSY); PatternFast(MyPtnLN); PatternFast(MyPtnSN); PatternNeutralFast(PtnNeutYes); PatternNeutralFast(PtnNeutYes2); PatternDirectionalFast(ptnDirYes); UAPtnBase(MyPtnLYExtra); ADX
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(152) [Default for MyPtnLY/MyPtnSY]:**
• Meaning: Always returns TRUE
• Trading use: No pattern restriction (allows all trades)

**PatternNeutralFast(55) [PtnNeutYes/PtnNeutYes2]:**
• Meaning: Uses PatternFast(55) = highd0 > (lowd0 + lowd0*1*0.01)
• Indicates: Current bar's high > low + 1% of low (minimum range requirement)
• Trading use: Ensures adequate volatility

**PatternDirectionalFast(34) [ptnDirYes]:**
• Meaning: Uses PatternFast(34) = (highd0-opend0) > (highd1-opend1)
• Indicates: Current bar's upper shadow > previous bar's upper shadow
• Trading use: Momentum confirmation for breakouts

**UAPtnBase Extra Patterns:**
• MyPtnLYExtra/MyPtnSYExtra default to pattern 41
• MyPtnLNExtra/MyPtnSNExtra default to pattern 42
• Pattern 41: (opend0-lowd0) > ((opend1-lowd1)*0.5) - lower shadow comparison
• Pattern 42: (opend0-lowd0) > (opend1-lowd1) - lower shadow strength

**ADX Filter:**
• ADX < 43 required for entry
• Indicates low trend strength/consolidation
• Sets up breakout conditions
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• **Comprehensive filtering system** with multiple pattern confirmations
• **Asymmetric risk management** - different stops/targets for long/short
• **Session-based logic** with proper OHLC calculation
• **ADX filter** prevents trading in trending markets
• **Time controls** and trade limits prevent overtrading
• **Flexible pattern system** allows extensive optimization

**WEAKNESSES:**
• **Extreme complexity** makes it difficult to understand/maintain
• **Over-optimization risk** with numerous parameters (20+ inputs)
• **Hard-coded magic numbers** without clear rationale
• **Asymmetric logic** may create unbalanced performance
• **Multiple pattern layers** could lead to very few trades
• **Limited documentation** on pattern selection reasoning

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• **Good:** Clear stops and targets for both sides
• **Good:** Maximum days in trade protection
• **Concern:** Large stop losses ($1700-$2200) relative to targets
• **Concern:** No position sizing based on volatility

**OVERALL:**
**Sophisticated but potentially over-engineered strategy**. The multiple pattern filters and ADX confirmation show thoughtful design, but the complexity may hurt robustness. **Asymmetric parameters suggest curve-fitting**. Would benefit from simplification and clearer logic documentation.

**WEAKNESSES:**

tags: Mean Reversion + Momentum Breakout with ATR Trailing
summary: A **dual-sided strategy** that combines mean reversion and momentum breakout signals using **ATR-based thresholds** and **price channel patterns**. The system goes short on gap-down reversals and long on momentum breakouts, with sophisticated **ATR dynamic trailing** stops.
entry_conditions:

• **Dynamic trailing stop** system preserves profits intelligently

**WEAKNESSES:**

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**

**OVERALL:**
A **sophisticated hybrid strategy** with intelligent volatility adaptation and asymmetric market approach. The **ATR-based logic** is well-designed, but the **lack of fixed stops** and **complex entry requirements** may limit practical effectiveness. pattern_details:

**WEAKNESSES:**

quality_analysis:

tags: Session Open Reversal with Pattern Confirmation
summary: This strategy trades **reversals** at the session open (19:00) using multi-timeframe confirmation. It waits for price to move away from the session open and then **reverse back through it**, confirmed by **directional and neutral patterns**. The strategy uses **15-minute bias** confirmation and has strict **one-trade-per-session** rules.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Session open at 19:00 establishes reference point
• Last 15-minute bar (data2) must be bullish (C>O)
• Price drops below session open after 19:00
• Price then rallies back above session open
• PatternDirectionalFast(+PtnDirYes) = true AND PatternDirectionalFast(+PtnDirNo) = false
• PatternNeutralFast(PtnNeutYes) = true AND PatternNeutralFast(PtnNeutNo) = false
• Time between 18:30-16:30
• MaxTradeLong = true (no existing long position)

**SHORT Entries:**
• Session open at 19:00 establishes reference point
• Last 15-minute bar (data2) must be bearish (C<O)
• Price rises above session open after 19:00
• Price then falls back below session open
• PatternDirectionalFast(-PtnDirYes) = true AND PatternDirectionalFast(-PtnDirNo) = false
• PatternNeutralFast(PtnNeutYes) = true AND PatternNeutralFast(PtnNeutNo) = false
• Time between 18:30-16:30
• MaxTradeShort = true (no existing short position)
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Long exits if price drops below (19:00 low - 30 points)
• Short exits if price rises above (19:00 high + 30 points)
• Maximum 2 days in trade - forced exit at 16:30-17:00

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: MyStop points (if > 0)
• Take profit: 50 points in currency
• Breakeven: 30 points in currency

**Time Exits:**
• SetExitOnClose active (session 18:00-16:59)
• Forced exit after maxdaysintrade (2 days) between 16:30-17:00
stop_loss_level:
• SetStopLoss(**MyStop * BigPointValue**) = MyStop in **currency**
• Currently set to 0 (no stop loss active)
time_exit_details: Exit between **16:30-17:00** after maximum 2 days in trade
pattern_details:
**PatternNeutralFast(55):** body1d < 0.1 * range1d (PatternFast case 55 maps to case 1)
• Meaning: Current bar body less than 10% of its range
• Indicates: Doji/spinning top, indecision
• Trading use: Neutral market condition for reversal setup

**PatternNeutralFast(27):** body5d > 0.9 * range5d (PatternFast case 27)
• Meaning: 5-day body greater than 90% of 5-day range
• Indicates: Strong directional movement over 5 days
• Trading use: Avoid entries when this is true (false condition)

**PatternDirectionalFast(52):** highd1<highd2 and lowd1<lowd2 (PatternFast case 52)
• Meaning: Yesterday's high and low both below previous day

**PatternDirectionalFast(35):** (highd0-opend0)> ((highd1-opend1)*1.5) (PatternFast case 35)
• Meaning: Today's upper wick 1.5x larger than yesterday's
• Indicates: Increased buying pressure/rejection
• Trading use: Avoid entries when this is true (false condition)
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Multi-timeframe confirmation (30-min execution, 15-min bias)
• Clear session-based logic with defined reference points
• Pattern-based entry filters reduce false signals
• Good risk management with breakeven and profit targets
• One-trade-per-session rule prevents overtrading
• Proper session handling for Gold futures

**WEAKNESSES:**

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**

• Position sizing fixed at 1 contract
• Maximum holding period limits exposure

**OVERALL:**
**High complexity** strategy with sophisticated pattern recognition but **dangerous risk profile** due to disabled stop loss. The **session open reversal concept** is sound for Gold, but requires proper **stop loss implementation** to be viable. Pattern combinations may be **over-optimized** without extensive out-of-sample testing.

tags: Session-based momentum breakout with wick comparison
summary: This is a **momentum breakout strategy** that trades when current session wicks (shadows) are significantly larger than previous session wicks. It uses **session-based OHLC data** and enters long when upper wicks expand and short when lower wicks expand, suggesting continuation of momentum.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Current session upper wick > 75% of previous session upper wick: (highd0-opend0) > (highd1-opend1)*0.75
• Not Monday (MyDOW ≠ 1)
• Time filter: NOT between 15:30-21:00
• Month filter: NOT July or August
• No significant close-to-close gap (±0.5%)
• Entry: Stop order at previous session high (highd1)

**SHORT Entries:**
• Current session lower wick > 75% of previous session lower wick: (opend0-lowd0) > (opend1-lowd1)*0.75
• Not Thursday (MyDOW ≠ 4)
• Same time, month, and gap filters as long
• Entry: Stop order at previous session low (lowd1)
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Manual stops: Long exits at entry - 7.5, Short exits at entry + 7.5
• Session close: Exit at open if time ≥ 16:54 or at session start
• Exit on close enabled

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 9.0 in **currency** (7.5 * 1.2 * bigpointvalue)
• Breakeven: 15.0 in **currency**
• Take profit: 45.0 in **currency**

**Time Exits:**
• Force exit between 16:54-18:00 at next open
• Exit at session start (18:00-17:15 next day)
time_exit_details: Exit at **16:54** and at **session start** (18:00)
function_patterns: Session OHLC calculation; Wick size comparison; Day-of-week filter; Time filter; Month exclusion filter
pattern_details:
**Session OHLC Function:** _OHLCMulti5(1800, 1715, ohlcValues)
• Meaning: Calculates session data from 18:00 to 17:15 next day
• Provides: Current and 5 previous sessions' OHLC data
• Trading use: Foundation for all entry calculations

**Upper Wick Expansion:** (highd0-opend0) > (highd1-opend1)*0.75
• Meaning: Current session's upper wick exceeds 75% of previous session's upper wick
• Indicates: Increasing upward pressure/momentum
• Trading use: Long breakout signal

**Lower Wick Expansion:** (opend0-lowd0) > (opend1-lowd1)*0.75
• Meaning: Current session's lower wick exceeds 75% of previous session's lower wick
• Indicates: Increasing downward pressure/momentum
• Trading use: Short breakout signal

**Gap Filter:** NOT (closed1 < closed2-0.5% OR closed1 > closed2+0.5%)
• Meaning: Avoids trading when significant gaps occur between sessions
• Indicates: Normal market continuation vs gap conditions
• Trading use: Risk management filter
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Innovative wick expansion concept for momentum detection
• Comprehensive risk management with stops, targets, and breakeven
• Smart session-based approach for futures trading
• Multiple filters (time, day, month, gap) reduce false signals
• Proper position management with one-trade-per-session logic

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Complex session calculation may be prone to data issues
• Day-of-week restrictions seem arbitrary (Monday/Thursday exclusions)
• No trend or volatility context - could trade against major moves
• Stop loss might be too tight for some instruments
• Month exclusions reduce trading opportunities significantly

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Well-defined stop loss at 9.0 currency units with 1.2x multiplier
• Breakeven at 15.0 and profit target at 45.0 provide 3:1 reward-risk
• Time-based exits prevent overnight exposure
• One position per session prevents overexposure

**OVERALL:**
This is a **solid momentum breakout system** with good risk management. The wick expansion concept is creative and the session-based approach suits futures well. However, the multiple arbitrary filters and tight stops may limit profitability. The **3:1 reward-risk ratio** is attractive, but success depends heavily on the wick expansion theory being valid in practice.

summary: This is a **multi-day trend-following breakout strategy** that enters long when price breaks above the highest high of the current or previous session, and short when breaking below the lowest low. function_patterns: PatternFast(55); PatternFast(56); PatternDirectionalFast(+52); PatternDirectionalFast(+14); PatternDirectionalFast(-52); PatternDirectionalFast(-14)
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(55):** (highd0>(lowd0+lowd0*1*0.01))
• Meaning: Current high > low + 1% of low price
• Indicates: Minimum daily range requirement
• Trading use: Volatility filter

**PatternFast(56):** (highd0>(lowd0+lowd0*1.5*0.01))

**PatternFast(14):** body5d < 1.5 * (highd5-lowd1)

quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Clear breakout logic with defined entry levels
• Multiple pattern filters to confirm market conditions
• Proper risk management with both stop loss and take profit
• Time-based maximum holding period prevents getting stuck in trades
• One entry per day rule prevents overtrading

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Complex pattern combinations may over-optimize and reduce trade frequency
• Large stop loss (1100) relative to profit target (2250) creates unfavorable risk-reward ratio
• Session times (19:00-13:00) seem unusual and may not align with natural market sessions
• No trend filter or market regime awareness

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Fixed stop loss and take profit provide clear risk parameters
• Maximum days in trade prevents indefinite holding
• Position sizing appears fixed at 1 contract

**OVERALL:**
This is a **moderately sophisticated breakout strategy** with extensive pattern filtering. The **risk-reward ratio of approximately 1:2** is reasonable, but the complex pattern requirements may significantly reduce trade frequency. The strategy would benefit from **clearer session definitions** and possibly **dynamic position sizing** based on volatility.

entry_conditions:

tags: Short-only session low breakout with volatility filters

**WEAKNESSES:**

tags: Session-based N-period High/Low Breakout with ADX Filter
summary: This is a **breakout strategy** that enters long when price breaks above the N-session highest high and short when breaking below the N-session lowest low. entry_conditions:

**SHORT Entries:**

function_patterns: PatternNeutralFast(55); PatternNeutralFast(45); PatternDirectionalFast(52); PatternDirectionalFast(-38); ADX Filter
pattern_details:
**PatternNeutralFast(55):** References PatternFast(55)
• Pattern 55: (highd0>(lowd0+lowd0*1*0.01))
• Meaning: Today's high > yesterday's low + 1% of yesterday's low
• Indicates: Minimal upward price movement requirement
• Trading use: Basic volatility filter

**PatternNeutralFast(45):** References PatternFast(45) - used as exclusion
• Pattern 45: ((opend0-lowd0)>((opend1-lowd1)*2.5))
• Meaning: Today's lower shadow > 2.5x yesterday's lower shadow
• Indicates: Significantly larger lower wick today
• Trading use: Avoid when today shows excessive downward rejection

**PatternDirectionalFast(52):** References PatternFast(52) for longs
• Pattern 52: (highd1<highd2 and lowd1<lowd2)
• Meaning: Yesterday's range completely below day before
• Indicates: Downward price compression
• Trading use: Breakout setup after compression

**PatternDirectionalFast(-38):** Inverse of Pattern 38 - used as exclusion
• Pattern 38: ((highd0-opend0)>((highd1-opend1)*3))
• Meaning: Today's upper shadow > 3x yesterday's upper shadow
• Indicates: Excessive upward rejection today
• Trading use: Avoid longs when excessive upper wick rejection present
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**

• Multiple timeframe analysis (N-session lookback)
• ADX filter prevents trading in overly trending markets
• Comprehensive risk management with stops, targets, and breakeven
• Time-based controls with trading windows and pause periods
• Session skip functionality for avoiding unfavorable days
• Professional code structure with proper session handling

**WEAKNESSES:**

• Pattern selection appears arbitrary without clear market logic
• Multiple filters may reduce trade frequency significantly
• ADX threshold of 40 is quite restrictive
• No position sizing based on volatility or risk
• Pattern combinations may create conflicting signals

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**

• 4:1 reward-to-risk ratio (4000 profit vs 1000 stop)
• Breakeven protection at 1000 currency units
• Maximum days in trade limit prevents extended exposure
• Time-based exits provide additional risk control

**OVERALL:**
This is a **sophisticated breakout strategy** with multiple layers of filtering. While the core breakout logic is sound and the risk management is comprehensive, the **complexity may lead to overfitting**. The strategy would benefit from simplification and clearer rationale for pattern selection. The **4:1 reward-to-risk ratio** is attractive, but the multiple filters may significantly reduce trade frequency.

tags: Moving Average Crossover with Daily Filter
summary: A **moving average crossover system** using 12/24 period SMAs on hourly crude oil data. Entries require **daily consolidation setups** and **gradient confirmation** to filter out weak signals and improve timing.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Previous day shows consolidation: |Close-Open|/(High-Low) ≤ 0.5 AND bullish (Close > Open)
• FastSMA (12) has strong gradient: |FastSMA change| ≥ 1.6 × |SlowSMA change| over 2 periods
• FastSMA crosses above SlowSMA
• No existing position

**SHORT Entries:**
• Previous day shows consolidation: |Close-Open|/(High-Low) ≤ 0.5 AND bearish (Close < Open)
• FastSMA (12) has strong gradient confirmation
• FastSMA crosses below SlowSMA
• No existing position
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Long positions: Exit when FastSMA crosses below SlowSMA
• Short positions: Exit when FastSMA crosses above SlowSMA

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 1500 in **currency**
• No take profit target

**Time Exits:**
• Friday exit on close
• Forced exit Friday 4:00-5:00 PM if still in position
time_exit_details: Exit on **Friday close** and forced exit **Friday 4:00-5:00 PM**
pattern_details:
**Daily Consolidation Pattern:**
• Formula: absvalue(CloseS(1)-OpenS(1))/(HighS(1)-LowS(1)) <= 0.5
• Meaning: Previous daily body is ≤50% of daily range
• Indicates: Consolidation day with potential for breakout
• Trading use: Setup filter - only trade after consolidation days

**Gradient Confirmation:**
• Formula: |FastSMA - FastSMA[2]| >= 1.6 × |SlowSMA - SlowSMA[2]|
• Meaning: Fast MA moving 1.6x faster than slow MA over 2 periods
• Indicates: Strong momentum building in fast average
• Trading use: Avoids weak/flat crossover signals

• Meaning: Today's open-to-high > 50% of yesterday's open-to-high
• Indicates: Upward pressure from open (must be FALSE for shorts)
• Trading use: Avoid conflicting upward gaps

• Meaning: Yesterday was completely below prior day (inside down)
• Indicates: Bearish consolidation or weakness
• Trading use: Directional bias confirmation

• Long positions: Exit at 15:00
• Short positions: Exit at 15:00

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 100 currency units
• Take profit: 300 currency units
• Breakeven: 90 currency units

**Time Exits:**
• Mandatory exit at 15:00 regardless of position type
time_exit_details: Exit at **15:00**
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(132):** lowd1 > lowd2
• Meaning: Yesterday's low is higher than day before yesterday's low
• Indicates: Higher low formation, potential upward bias
• Trading use: Long entry confirmation

**PatternFast(133):** highd1 < highd2 OR lowd1 > lowd2
• Meaning: Either lower high OR higher low compared to previous day
• Indicates: Inside day or consolidation pattern
• Trading use: Short entry confirmation for breakout

**PatternFast(153):** Not defined in function (>152 returns false)
• Meaning: Always returns false
• Indicates: Non-existent pattern
• Trading use: Effectively no additional filter
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Well-defined Donchian breakout system with clear logic
• Blast-off filter reduces false breakouts by requiring low volatility setup
• Proper risk management with stop loss, take profit, and breakeven
• Time-based exit prevents overnight exposure
• Session-based OHLC calculation for consistent reference levels

**WEAKNESSES:**
• PatternFast(153) is non-existent, making those conditions meaningless
• Asymmetric pattern logic between long/short entries may create bias
• Fixed 88-period lookback may not adapt to changing market conditions
• No volume or additional confirmation filters
• Skip day logic uses negative values which may cause issues

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Good risk/reward ratio (1:3 stop to target)
• Breakeven feature protects capital after favorable movement
• Single contract position sizing limits exposure
• Daily entry limit prevents over-trading

**OVERALL:**
Solid **breakout strategy foundation** with reasonable risk controls. The blast-off filter adds value by requiring consolidation before breakouts. However, the **pattern logic needs review** due to non-existent pattern 153, and the asymmetric entry conditions may need balancing.

tags: Mean Reversion with Moving Average Crosses
summary: A **long-only reversal strategy** that buys when price crosses under a 3-period average of lows while price is below its 10-period close, then exits when price crosses above a 3-period average of highs. Uses **day-of-week filtering** and time-based exits.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Close crosses under 3-period average of Low
• Close < Close[10] (price below 10-bar close)
• Day of week ≠ DayFilter (1 = Sunday excluded)
• Enter next bar at market

**SHORT Entries:**
• None - long-only strategy
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Close crosses over 3-period average of High
• Exit next bar at market

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: $2,500 in currency
• Take profit: $6,250 in currency

**Time Exits:**
• Exit after 14 bars since entry (MaxBars)
time_exit_details: Exit after **14 bars** since entry
pattern_details:
**AverageFC(Low, 3):** 3-period moving average of low prices
• Meaning: Short-term support level
• Indicates: Recent price floor
• Trading use: Entry trigger when crossed below

**AverageFC(High, 3):** 3-period moving average of high prices
• Meaning: Short-term resistance level
• Indicates: Recent price ceiling
• Trading use: Exit trigger when crossed above

**Close[Length]:** Close price 10 bars ago
• Meaning: Medium-term price reference
• Indicates: Trend context filter
• Trading use: Ensures bearish context for reversal entry
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Clear mean reversion logic with dual moving average system
• Good risk management with both stop loss and profit target
• Time-based exit prevents extended drawdowns
• Day-of-week filter adds market condition awareness
• Uses 480-minute bars reducing noise

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Long-only strategy misses short opportunities
• Simple moving averages may generate false signals
• No volatility or market condition filters
• Fixed stop/target ratios may not adapt to market conditions
• Limited to single contract position sizing

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• 2.5:1 reward-to-risk ratio ($6,250 profit vs $2,500 stop)
• Maximum 14-bar exposure limits time risk
• SetStopContract ensures proper execution

**OVERALL:**
A **straightforward mean reversion system** with reasonable risk controls but **limited sophistication**. The strategy shows good basic structure but lacks adaptive elements for changing market conditions.

tags: False Breakout Reversal
summary: This is a **mean reverting intraday strategy** that exploits false breakouts of previous day's high/low levels. It enters positions after price breaks out and then **reverses back through the trigger level**, betting against the breakout direction with **trailing stops** instead of fixed exits.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Time window: 20:00-15:30 (excluding 01:30-04:00 pause)
• Previous close below trigger (yesterday's low - LevelShift) AND current close above trigger
• UAPtnBase(41) = TRUE and UAPtnBase(42) = FALSE
• PatternNeutralFast(55) = TRUE twice and PatternNeutralFast(52) = FALSE
• PatternDirectionalFast(+52) = TRUE and two other directional patterns = FALSE
• Volatility expansion filter: price move > range expansion threshold
• Maximum 2 trades per day, skip specified session

**SHORT Entries:**
• Same time window and session limits
• Previous close above trigger (yesterday's high + LevelShift) AND current close below trigger
• UAPtnBase(23) = TRUE and UAPtnBase(42) = FALSE
• Same neutral pattern filters
• PatternDirectionalFast(-52) = TRUE with other directional patterns = FALSE
• Same volatility expansion requirement
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Trailing stop after 10 bars since entry
• Long: Sell at highest close since entry minus stop amount
• Short: Cover at lowest close since entry plus stop amount

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 1400 in currency
• No fixed profit target (MyProfit=0)
• Optional breakeven setting (MyBreakeven=0)

**Time Exits:**
• End of day exit between 16:30-16:45
• Maximum days in trade: 1 day (intraday only)
• Flat at 16:45 if still in position

**Profit-Based Exits:**
• Long exit when profit > 2000 and PatternDirectionalFast(-29) = TRUE
• Short exit when profit > 2000 and PatternDirectionalFast(52) = TRUE
take_profit_level: None (uses trailing stops and profit-based pattern exits)
time_exit_details: Exit between **16:30-16:45** for end of day
function_patterns: UAPtnBase(41); UAPtnBase(42); UAPtnBase(23); PatternNeutralFast(55); PatternNeutralFast(52); PatternDirectionalFast(52); PatternDirectionalFast(-29); PatternDirectionalFast(37); PatternDirectionalFast(38)
pattern_details:
**PatternNeutralFast(55):** ((highd0>(lowd0+lowd0*1.5*0.01)))
• Meaning: Today's high > today's low + 1.5% of low
• Indicates: Minimum daily range requirement
• Trading use: Volatility filter

**PatternNeutralFast(52):** (highd1<highd2 and lowd1<lowd2)
• Meaning: Yesterday's range completely inside day before
• Indicates: Inside day/consolidation
• Trading use: Avoided as filter (=FALSE required)

**UAPtnBase(41):** ((opend0-lowd0)> ((opend1-lowd1)*0.5))
• Meaning: Today's lower shadow > 50% of yesterday's lower shadow
• Indicates: Support rejection strength
• Trading use: Long entry confirmation

**UAPtnBase(42):** ((opend0-lowd0)> ((opend1-lowd1)*1))
• Meaning: Today's lower shadow > yesterday's lower shadow
• Indicates: Strong support rejection
• Trading use: Filter (must be FALSE for entries)

**UAPtnBase(23):** (body5d < 0.1 * range5d)
• Meaning: 5-day body < 10% of 5-day range
• Indicates: Extreme consolidation
• Trading use: Low volatility breakout setup

**PatternDirectionalFast(52/-52):** Same as pattern 52 but directional
• Meaning: Inside day pattern used directionally
• Trading use: Trend/counter-trend confirmation

**PatternDirectionalFast(-29):** Inverse of pattern 29
• Used for profit-taking on long positions when bearish signal appears
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Well-defined false breakout logic with clear trigger levels
• Multiple pattern filters reduce false signals
• Intelligent trailing stop system after 10 bars
• Comprehensive risk management with daily limits
• Volatility expansion filter improves entry timing
• Session-based logic appropriate for intraday trading

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Extremely complex entry conditions may over-optimize
• No fixed profit target relies entirely on trailing stops
• Multiple pattern dependencies create fragile logic
• LevelShift parameter needs careful optimization
• Pattern combinations may conflict or be redundant
• High complexity makes backtesting and validation difficult

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Fixed 1400 currency stop loss provides downside protection
• Maximum 2 trades per day prevents overtrading
• Intraday-only approach limits overnight risk
• Position sizing controlled via mycontracts input
• Trailing stops lock in profits after initial movement

**OVERALL:**
This is a **sophisticated mean reversion system** with sound theoretical foundation but **excessive complexity**. The false breakout concept is valid, but the numerous pattern filters may create an over-fitted strategy. The **trailing stop mechanism** is well-designed, but lack of fixed profit targets could limit upside capture. Would benefit from **simplification** while retaining core breakout reversal logic.

tags: Session-based breakout with pattern filtering
summary: This is a **session-based breakout strategy** that trades breakouts of overnight high/low levels during specific trading hours. It uses **pattern filtering** to confirm entries and avoid false breakouts with opposing patterns.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Time window: 04:00-09:00, excluding pause period 12:00-11:00
• Pattern confirmation: MyPtnLY (default 12) must be TRUE
• Pattern filter: MyPtnLN (default 35) must be FALSE
• Position filter: No long position in previous 2 bars
• Entry: Buy stop at session high (19:00-13:20)

**SHORT Entries:**
• Time window: 04:00-09:00, excluding pause period 12:00-11:00
• Pattern confirmation: MyPtnSY (default 12) must be TRUE
• Pattern filter: MyPtnSN (default 35) must be FALSE
• Position filter: No short position in previous 2 bars
• Entry: Sell stop at session low (19:00-13:20)
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• No specific exit logic defined

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 1250 in currency
• Take profit: 3000 in currency

**Time Exits:**
• Trading paused from 12:00-11:00 (likely next day)
time_exit_details: Trading restricted outside **04:00-09:00** window and paused during **12:00-11:00**
pattern_details:
**PtnBaseSA2(12):** Pattern 12 from PatternFast
• Definition: body5d < 0.75 * (highd5-lowd1)
• Meaning: 5-day body less than 75% of high-to-low range
• Indicates: Moderate consolidation pattern
• Trading use: Entry confirmation for breakouts

**PtnBaseSA2(35):** Pattern 35 from PatternFast
• Definition: (highd0-opend0) > ((highd1-opend1)*1.5)
• Meaning: Today's upper wick 1.5x larger than yesterday's
• Indicates: Strong rejection at higher levels
• Trading use: Filter to avoid entries when rejection present
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Clear session-based breakout logic with defined levels
• Pattern filtering reduces false breakouts
• Reasonable risk/reward ratio (1250 stop vs 3000 target = 1:2.4)
• Time-based controls prevent trading during unfavorable periods
• Position state checking prevents overexposure

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Relies heavily on overnight gaps which may be less reliable
• No adaptive stop loss or trailing mechanism
• Limited exit flexibility beyond stop/target
• Pattern logic may be overly complex for the core breakout concept

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Fixed stop loss provides clear risk control
• Position filters prevent pyramiding
• Time restrictions limit exposure periods

**OVERALL:**
Solid **session breakout strategy** with good risk management. The pattern filtering adds sophistication but may also reduce trade frequency. The **1:2.4 risk/reward ratio** is attractive for breakout trading.

tags: Daily momentum breakout with volatility-based exits
summary: A **time-based breakout strategy** that enters long positions at **4:00 PM** based on pattern conditions. Uses **variable position sizing** (double contracts if current close is below opening) and **volatility-based stops/targets** with ATR calculations.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Time must equal **1600** (4:00 PM)
• Day of week must NOT equal **dow** input (excludes specific weekday)
• No current market position (mp = 0)
• Must satisfy ONE of three pattern conditions:
  - PtnBaseSA(16) OR
  - PtnBaseSA(29) OR
  - PtnBaseSA(18)
• Entry: Buy at **current close as limit price**
• Position size: **2 contracts** if C < Open[0], otherwise **1 contract**

**SHORT Entries:**
• None - long-only strategy
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• **Time exit**: After **kcount** bars (default 10 bars)
• Exit at market on next bar

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• **Profit target**: Low + kprf*ATR(3) = Low + **2.5***ATR(3) as limit
• **Stop loss**: High - kstp*ATR(3) = High - **5.5***ATR(3) as stop
• Both based on **3-period Average True Range**

**Time Exits:**
• Position closed after **10 bars** (kcount parameter)
stop_loss_level:
• **Dynamic ATR-based**: High - **5.5** * ATR(3) in **points**
• **Trailing nature**: Adjusts with each bar's high
take_profit_level:
• **Dynamic ATR-based**: Low + **2.5** * ATR(3) in **points**
• **Trailing nature**: Adjusts with each bar's low
time_exit_details: Exit after **10 bars** (kcount parameter) at market
pattern_details:
**NOTE:** PtnBaseSA() function is **not provided** in the available function library. This appears to be a **custom pattern function** not included in the standard PatternFast definitions.

**PtnBaseSA(16):** Unknown pattern - function not available
• Meaning: Cannot determine without function definition
• Indicates: Unknown
• Trading use: Entry condition trigger

**PtnBaseSA(29):** Unknown pattern - function not available
• Meaning: Cannot determine without function definition
• Indicates: Unknown
• Trading use: Entry condition trigger

**PtnBaseSA(18):** Unknown pattern - function not available
• Meaning: Cannot determine without function definition
• Indicates: Unknown
• Trading use: Entry condition trigger
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• **Variable position sizing** based on price action (smart risk scaling)
• **Volatility-based exits** using ATR for dynamic stop/target levels
• **Time-based entry** provides consistency and discipline
• **Multiple exit conditions** (time, profit, stop) for good risk management
• **Asymmetric risk/reward** with 2.5 ATR profit vs 5.5 ATR stop

**WEAKNESSES:**
• **Unknown pattern functions** - cannot evaluate entry logic quality
• **Fixed time entry** may miss better setups at other times
• **No trend filter** - may trade against major market direction
• **Hard-coded parameters** reduce adaptability
• **Day-of-week exclusion** seems arbitrary without justification
• **60-minute bars only** limits flexibility

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• **Poor risk/reward ratio** - stop loss (5.5 ATR) is much larger than profit target (2.5 ATR)
• **Position sizing** helps but doesn't offset unfavorable R:R
• **Time exit** prevents indefinite holding but may exit prematurely

**OVERALL:**
**Below average strategy** due to **unknown entry patterns** and **poor risk/reward profile**. The 5.5:2.5 ATR ratio means risking more than twice the potential gain, requiring >69% win rate to be profitable. Good framework with **dynamic exits** but needs **better entry logic** and **improved risk/reward balance**.

tags: Gap Reversal with Pattern Confirmation
summary: This is a **gap reversal strategy** that trades against significant price gaps at market open. When there's a **gap down > 0.3%**, it buys on a break above the previous hour's high. When there's a **gap up > 1%**, it sells on a break below the previous hour's low. Pattern confirmation is required for entries.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Gap down > 0.3% from previous close
• Time between 12:00-13:00
• No entries today yet
• PatternFast(41) = TRUE (pattern confirmation)
• PatternFast(31) = FALSE (pattern filter)
• Price breaks above previous hour's high (data2)

**SHORT Entries:**
• Gap up > 1% from previous close
• Time between 12:00-13:00
• No entries today yet
• PatternFast(41) = TRUE (pattern confirmation)
• PatternFast(21) = FALSE (pattern filter)
• Price breaks below previous hour's low (data2)
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Maximum 4 days in trade (forced exit at 21:00)
• Exit on close if max days reached

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Dynamic ATR-based stop loss
• Fixed profit target
• Optional breakeven

**Time Exits:**
• Forced exit at 21:00 if maximum days in trade reached
stop_loss_level:
• **Dynamic:** Min(ATR(4) × 2 × BigPointValue, 105 × BigPointValue) in **currency**
• Uses 4-period ATR from 60-min data with 2x multiplier
• Capped at maximum 105 currency units
time_exit_details: Exit at **21:00** if maximum days in trade (4) is reached
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(41):** ((opend0-lowd0)> ((opend1-lowd1)*0.5))
• Meaning: Today's lower shadow > 0.5× yesterday's lower shadow
• Indicates: Increased downside rejection/support
• Trading use: Bullish pattern confirmation

**PatternFast(31):** ((highd0-opend0)> ((highd1-opend1)*0.25))
• Meaning: Today's upper shadow > 0.25× yesterday's upper shadow
• Indicates: Upside rejection/resistance
• Trading use: Filter to avoid entries when resistance present

**PatternFast(21):** body5d > 2 * (highd5-lowd1)
• Meaning: 5-day body > 2× range from 5 days ago high to yesterday low
• Indicates: Very strong directional movement
• Trading use: Filter for short entries
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• **Smart gap logic:** Different thresholds for up/down gaps (asymmetric)
• **Multi-timeframe approach:** 30-min entries, 60-min ATR and reference levels
• **Dynamic risk management:** ATR-based stops with maximum cap
• **Pattern confirmation:** Uses multiple pattern filters to improve entry quality
• **Time-based risk control:** Maximum days in trade prevents runaway losses

**WEAKNESSES:**
• **Narrow time window:** Only 1-hour entry window may miss opportunities
• **Complex pattern logic:** Multiple pattern combinations may over-optimize
• **Gap thresholds unclear:** 0.3% vs 1% asymmetry needs justification
• **Limited session coverage:** Only trades during specific European hours

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• **Good:** Dynamic ATR stops adapt to volatility
• **Good:** Maximum loss cap prevents extreme stops
• **Adequate:** Time-based exit prevents indefinite holding
• **Concern:** Large profit target (700) vs capped stop may create poor risk/reward

**OVERALL:**
This is a **well-structured gap reversal system** with sophisticated risk management. The **multi-timeframe approach** and **pattern confirmation** show good design principles. However, the **narrow trading window** and **asymmetric gap thresholds** may limit effectiveness. The strategy appears **over-engineered** with multiple pattern filters that could lead to curve-fitting.

tags: Channel Breakout with ADX Filter
summary: **Crypto-focused breakout strategy** that enters long above highest high and short below lowest low of N periods. Uses **ADX filtering** for trend strength and **pattern filters** to reduce false signals. Designed specifically for volatile crypto markets with **ATR-based position sizing**.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• No entries today yet (EntriesToday = 0)
• PatternNeutralFastSa(34) = true AND PatternNeutralFastSa(56) = false
• MarketPosition <= 0
• ADX(5) >= 22 (trend strength filter)
• PatternDirectionalFastSa(52) = true AND PatternDirectionalFastSa(53) = false
• Buy at UpperChannel (highest high of 7 periods) on stop

**SHORT Entries:**
• No entries today yet (EntriesToday = 0)
• PatternNeutralFastSa(34) = true AND PatternNeutralFastSa(56) = false
• MarketPosition >= 0
• ADX(5) >= 22 (trend strength filter)
• PatternDirectionalFastSa(-52) = true AND PatternDirectionalFastSa(-53) = false
• Sell short at LowerChannel (lowest low of 7 periods) on stop
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• LONG: Sell at low[2] (2 bars ago low) on stop
• SHORT: Buy to cover at high[2] (2 bars ago high) on stop

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop Loss: ATR-based, applied after entry bar
• Take Profit: ATR-based, applied after entry bar
• LONG Stop: (Position Size × ATR(3) × BigPointValue) × 0.2
• SHORT Stop: (Position Size × ATR(3) × BigPointValue) × 0.2
• LONG Target: (Position Size × ATR(3) × BigPointValue) × 5.0
• SHORT Target: (Position Size × ATR(3) × BigPointValue) × 1.0

**Time Exits:**
• Maximum 5 bars in trade (MaxBarsInTrade)
• Exit at market after 5 bars regardless of P&L
stop_loss_level:
• Dynamic ATR-based stop in **currency**
• LONG: **(Position Size × ATR × BigPointValue) × 0.2** in **currency**
• SHORT: **(Position Size × ATR × BigPointValue) × 0.2** in **currency**
take_profit_level:
• Dynamic ATR-based target in **currency**
• LONG: **(Position Size × ATR × BigPointValue) × 5.0** in **currency**
• SHORT: **(Position Size × ATR × BigPointValue) × 1.0** in **currency**
time_exit_details: Exit at market after **5 bars** maximum holding period
function_patterns: ADX(5); AvgTrueRange(3); PatternNeutralFastSa(34); PatternNeutralFastSa(56); PatternDirectionalFastSa(52); PatternDirectionalFastSa(53)
pattern_details:
**PatternNeutralFastSa(34):** Based on PatternFast(34)
• Pattern 34: (highd0-opend0)> ((highd1-opend1)*1)
• Meaning: Today's upper wick is larger than yesterday's upper wick
• Indicates: Increased buying pressure/rejection at higher levels
• Trading use: Neutral pattern for entry qualification

**PatternNeutralFastSa(56):** Based on PatternFast(56)
• Pattern 56: (highd0>(lowd0+lowd0*1.5*0.01))
• Meaning: Today's high > low + 1.5% of low
• Indicates: Minimum daily range requirement (1.5%)
• Trading use: Volatility filter (used as exclusion when true)

**PatternDirectionalFastSa(52):** Based on PatternFast(52)
• Pattern 52: highd1<highd2 and lowd1<lowd2
• Meaning: Yesterday's range completely below day before
• Indicates: Downward price action/consolidation
• Trading use: Directional bias confirmation

**PatternDirectionalFastSa(53):** Based on PatternFast(53)
• Pattern 53: (highd0>(lowd0+lowd0*0.5*0.01))
• Meaning: Today's high > low + 0.5% of low
• Indicates: Minimum intraday range (0.5%)
• Trading use: Activity filter (used as exclusion when true)
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• **ADX trend filter** prevents trading in choppy markets
• **ATR-based position sizing** adapts to volatility
• **Asymmetric profit targets** (5:1 vs 1:1) account for directional bias
• **Multiple pattern filters** reduce false signals
• **Hard stop at high[2]/low[2]** provides concrete risk management
• **Maximum holding period** prevents extended drawdowns

**WEAKNESSES:**
• **Complex pattern logic** may over-optimize to historical data
• **Asymmetric targets** suggest potential bias issues
• **No breakeven or trailing stops** to protect profits
• **Single timeframe** approach misses multi-timeframe confirmation
• **Pattern combinations** create very specific entry conditions that may not generalize

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• **Good:** ATR-based stops adapt to market volatility
• **Good:** Position sizing based on risk percentage
• **Concern:** Stop only applied after entry bar increases risk
• **Concern:** Very tight stops (0.2x ATR) may cause premature exits

**OVERALL:**
**Well-structured breakout system** with sophisticated filtering but may be **over-engineered** for crypto markets. The **asymmetric profit targets** and **complex pattern requirements** suggest potential curve-fitting. **Risk management is adequate** but the **tight stops combined with crypto volatility** could be problematic.

tags: Pivot/Support-Resistance Breakout with Pattern Filtering
summary: A **breakout strategy** that trades breaks of previous day's high/low or pivot levels (R1/S1) with multiple pattern filters. Uses **complex pattern combinations** to filter entries and includes day-of-week restrictions.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• PatternNeutralFast(4) = TRUE AND PatternNeutralFast(1) = FALSE
• Day of week ≠ Monday (mydayNolong=1)
• UAPtnBase(41) = TRUE AND UAPtnBase(42) = FALSE
• PatternDirectionalFast(+49) = TRUE
• Previous close below trigger AND current close above trigger
• Within trading time window (2300-1600)

**SHORT Entries:**
• PatternNeutralFast(4) = TRUE AND PatternNeutralFast(1) = FALSE
• Day of week ≠ Friday (mydayNoshort=5)
• UAPtnBase(41) = TRUE AND UAPtnBase(42) = FALSE
• PatternDirectionalFast(-49) = TRUE
• Previous close above trigger AND current close below trigger
• Within trading time window (2300-1600)
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• End of session exit if ID=0
• Position closed at MyEndTime

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 1100 currency units
• Take profit: 5000 currency units

**Time Exits:**
• Positions closed at calculated end time or CloseAtTime if specified
time_exit_details: Exit at calculated **MyEndTime** or specific **CloseAtTime** if set
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(4):** body1d < 0.75 * range1d
• Meaning: Yesterday's body less than 75% of range
• Indicates: Moderate consolidation with some wicks
• Trading use: Allows for breakout setup

**PatternFast(1):** body1d < 0.1 * range1d
• Meaning: Yesterday's body less than 10% of range
• Indicates: Very tight consolidation, doji-like
• Trading use: Avoided (=FALSE) to prevent low-volatility periods

**PatternFast(41):** (opend0-lowd0)> ((opend1-lowd1)*0.5)
• Meaning: Today's lower wick > 50% of yesterday's lower wick
• Indicates: Increased buying pressure at lows
• Trading use: Confirms strength pattern

**PatternFast(42):** (opend0-lowd0)> ((opend1-lowd1)*1)
• Meaning: Today's lower wick > yesterday's lower wick
• Indicates: Strong buying at lows
• Trading use: Avoided (=FALSE) to prevent over-filtering

**PatternFast(49):** closed1>closed2 and closed2>closed3 and closed3>closed4 and closed4 > closed5
• Meaning: Four consecutive higher closes
• Indicates: Strong upward momentum over 4 days
• Trading use: Directional bias confirmation (+49 for long, -49 for short)
number_of_patterns: 5 pattern functions with complex logic combinations
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Multiple pattern filters reduce false breakouts
• Day-of-week restrictions based on market behavior
• Flexible level choice (pivot vs high/low)
• Good risk management with defined stops/targets
• Session-based OHLC calculation for accuracy

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Extremely complex entry conditions may over-optimize
• Pattern combinations not clearly justified
• High complexity may lead to curve fitting
• Limited trading opportunities due to multiple filters
• Pattern logic mixing different timeframes without clear rationale

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Fixed stop loss at 1100 currency units (reasonable)
• Take profit at 5000 currency units (4.5:1 reward/risk ratio)
• Position sizing controlled via MyContracts input
• Time-based exits prevent overnight exposure

**OVERALL:**
This is a **sophisticated but potentially over-engineered** breakout strategy. While the individual components make sense, the **combination of 5+ pattern conditions** creates extreme complexity that may not translate to robust live performance. The **4.5:1 reward/risk ratio** is attractive, but the multiple filters may significantly reduce trade frequency. Strategy would benefit from **simplification and clearer logic justification**.

tags: Donchian Channel Breakout with Pattern Filters
summary: A **Donchian channel breakout** strategy that enters long on breakouts above the highest high and short on breakouts below the lowest low of a 92-period lookback. The strategy uses **multiple pattern filters** including blast-off conditions and compression filters to qualify entries during a specific trading window.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Time window: 20:00-16:45
• Max 1 entry per day
• PatternNeutralFast(55) = TRUE AND PatternNeutralFast(56) = FALSE
• Day is not skipdayL
• PatternDirectionalFast(+52) = TRUE AND PatternDirectionalFast(+53) = FALSE
• Blast-off filter: Previous bar body < 30% of range
• Compression filter active
• Buy at previous bar's Donchian high (92-period)

**SHORT Entries:**
• Same time and pattern conditions as long
• Day is not skipdayS
• PatternDirectionalFast(-52) = TRUE AND PatternDirectionalFast(-53) = FALSE

**SHORT Entries:**
• Current bar closes below open (c < o)
• Previous bar closed below open (c[1] < o[1])
• Short-term ATR(2) > Medium-term ATR(2)[18] * 3
• Must be within trading hours (8:30 AM to 2:30 PM)
• Two consecutive red bars during high volatility period
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Exit on close enabled

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Dynamic stop loss: Lesser of static stop (1250) or parametric stop
• Profit target: Entry price minus (ATR * 8)

**Time Exits:**
• Forced exit at market close
stop_loss_level:
• Dynamic: **min(1250, (entryprice + ATR * 1) * bigpointvalue)** in **currency**
• Uses lesser of static 1250 or ATR-based calculation
take_profit_level:
• **Entry price - (ATR * 8)** as limit order
• ATR-based multiple for profit target
time_exit_details: Exit at **market close** via setexitonclose
pattern_details:
**AvgTrueRange(2):** Short-term volatility measure
• Meaning: 2-period Average True Range
• Indicates: Recent price volatility
• Trading use: Entry filter and position sizing

**AvgTrueRange[2](18):** Medium-term volatility baseline
• Meaning: 2-period ATR displaced 18 bars ago
• Indicates: Historical volatility comparison
• Trading use: Volatility expansion detection

**TW(830,1430):** Time window function
• Meaning: Trading allowed between 8:30 AM - 2:30 PM
• Indicates: Active market hours
• Trading use: Session-based filtering
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Smart volatility expansion filter prevents trades in quiet markets
• Dynamic stop loss adapts to market conditions with safety cap
• Reasonable risk-reward ratio (1:8 stop to target)
• Session-based filtering avoids low-liquidity periods
• Short bias appropriate for volatility expansion scenarios

**WEAKNESSES:**
• No position sizing based on volatility
• Single ATR lookback period may be too short
• No trend filter - could short into strong uptrends
• Static maximum stop may be too large for some instruments
• Lacks volatility regime classification

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Good: Dynamic stops with static maximum
• Good: Profit targets based on market volatility
• Concern: Large static stop (1250) could create oversized risk

**OVERALL:**
**Well-conceived volatility strategy** with solid risk management framework. The volatility expansion filter is sophisticated, but strategy would benefit from **trend awareness** and **dynamic position sizing**. Good foundation for short-term mean reversion during volatile periods.

tags: Long-only Pattern-Based Breakout with High-of-N-Bars Entry
summary: A **long-only breakout strategy** that trades Monday through Wednesday only. Uses **pattern confirmation** (consolidation pattern must be true, rejection pattern must be false) before entering on breakout above the **16-bar high**. Features comprehensive risk management with stop loss, profit target, and time-based exit.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Time window: **16:00 to 21:45** (excluding pause 12:00-11:00)
• Pattern condition: **PtnBaseSA2(PtnLY,ohlcvalues)** = TRUE
• Pattern rejection: **PtnBaseSA2(PtnLN,ohlcvalues)** = FALSE
• Day filter: **Monday through Wednesday only**
• Max entries: **1 per calendar day**
• Entry trigger: **Buy next bar at highest(h,16) stop**
• Test phase bypass available

**SHORT Entries:**
• None - Long only strategy
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Time exit: **21:45 on Wednesdays only**

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: **2000 currency units**
• Take profit: **8000 currency units**
• Breakeven stop: **Disabled (0)**

**Time Exits:**
• Forced exit at **21:45 on Wednesday** (end of trading week)
time_exit_details: Exit at **21:45 on Wednesday only**
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(23):** body5d < 0.1 * range5d
• Meaning: 5-day body is less than 10% of 5-day range
• Indicates: Extreme consolidation, very low volatility
• Trading use: Breakout setup condition - market coiled for move

**PatternFast(31):** (highd0-opend0) > ((highd1-opend1)*0.25)
• Meaning: Today's upper shadow > 25% of yesterday's upper shadow
• Indicates: Increased intraday volatility or rejection at highs
• Trading use: Rejection filter - strategy avoids entry when this is true
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Clear pattern-based entry logic with confirmation and rejection filters
• Conservative day-of-week filter (Mon-Wed only) reduces weekend risk
• Excellent risk management: 1:4 risk-reward ratio (2000 stop vs 8000 target)
• Position sizing control and daily entry limits
• Comprehensive time filtering with trading window and pause periods

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Long-only bias misses short opportunities and has directional risk
• Limited to 3 trading days per week, potentially missing opportunities
• Pattern definitions may be too restrictive, limiting trade frequency
• No adaptive stop loss or trailing mechanism
• High profit target (8000) may be difficult to achieve consistently

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Fixed stop loss of 2000 currency units provides clear risk control
• Daily entry limits prevent over-trading
• Time-based exit on Wednesday prevents weekend gaps
• Pattern rejection filter helps avoid false breakouts

**OVERALL:**
Well-structured breakout strategy with **solid risk management** and **conservative approach**. The pattern-based filtering and day-of-week restrictions show disciplined design, though the **long-only bias** and **high profit target** may limit performance. Good foundation that could benefit from **adaptive elements** and **short-side opportunities**.

tags: Weekly Range Breakout with Pattern Filter
summary: This is a **weekly range breakout strategy** that trades breakouts above/below the previous week's high/low during Asian session hours. It uses **PatternFast(14)** as a filter condition and includes strict **risk management** with defined stops and targets.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Time window: 00:00 to 09:00
• Maximum 1 trade per session (1800-1700)
• PatternFast(14) pattern condition met
• Close > previous week's high (HighW(1))
• Not already long

**SHORT Entries:**
• Time window: 00:00 to 09:00
• Maximum 1 trade per session (1800-1700)
• PatternFast(14) pattern condition met
• Close < previous week's low (LowW(1))
• Not already short
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• None specified

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 1100 in currency
• Take profit: 3500 in currency

**Time Exits:**
• All positions closed on Friday at 10:30
time_exit_details: Exit at **Friday 10:30**
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(14):** body5d < 1.5 * (highd5-lowd1)
• Meaning: 5-day body size compared to range from 5 days ago high to 1 day ago low
• Indicates: Moderate consolidation pattern, body contained within recent range
• Trading use: Filter for breakout setups, ensures price isn't overly extended

**_OHLCMulti5:** Session OHLC calculator
• Meaning: Calculates session-based OHLC values for last 5 sessions
• Session: 1800-1700 (18:00 to 17:00)
• Trading use: Provides historical session data for pattern analysis

**HighW(1)/LowW(1):** Weekly high/low references
• Meaning: Previous week's highest high and lowest low
• Indicates: Key weekly support/resistance levels
• Trading use: Breakout trigger levels
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Clear weekly breakout logic with defined timeframe
• Good risk management with 1:3.18 risk/reward ratio
• Trade frequency control (max 1 per session)
• Time-based exit prevents weekend risk
• Pattern filter adds confluence

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Limited to Asian session hours only
• Weekly breakouts can be prone to false signals
• PatternFast(14) filter logic may be too restrictive
• No trend bias or market condition filters
• Fixed stops/targets don't adapt to volatility

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Fixed stop loss of 1100 currency units
• Take profit at 3500 currency units (good risk/reward)
• Position sizing controlled via Size input
• Friday exit prevents weekend gaps

**OVERALL:**
Solid **medium-complexity breakout strategy** with decent risk management. The weekly range approach is logical, but success depends heavily on **market volatility** and **trend conditions**. Pattern filter adds some sophistication but needs backtesting validation.

tags: Session-based intraday breakout with pattern filtering
summary: A sophisticated **intraday breakout strategy** that trades session highs/lows with extensive **pattern filtering** and flexible risk management. Uses **151 candlestick patterns** to confirm entry conditions and filter false breakouts.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Price breaks above session high (myle + offset)
• Pattern confirmation: UAPtnBase(PtnLY=41) = TRUE
• Pattern filter: UAPtnBase(PtnLN=42) = FALSE
• Directional pattern: PatternDirectionalFast(+49) = TRUE
• Directional filter: PatternDirectionalFast(+29) = FALSE
• Neutral pattern: PatternNeutralFast(40) = TRUE
• Neutral filter: PatternNeutralFast(52) = FALSE
• Within time window and trading session
• Month/day restrictions apply

**SHORT Entries:**
• Price breaks below session low (myse + offset)
• Pattern confirmation: UAPtnBase(PtnSY=41) = TRUE
• Pattern filter: UAPtnBase(PtnSN=42) = FALSE
• Directional pattern: PatternDirectionalFast(-49) = TRUE
• Directional filter: PatternDirectionalFast(-29) = FALSE
• Same neutral pattern conditions as long
• Within time window and trading session
• Month/day restrictions apply
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• End of session exit at MyEndTime
• Maximum days in trade reached

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 2700 currency (default) or asymmetric (1700 long/short)
• Take profit: 5000 currency (default) or asymmetric (2200 long, 5400 short)
• Breakeven available but set to 0

**Time Exits:**
• End of session closure
• Maximum 7 days in trade with time-based flat (1800)
stop_loss_level:
• SetStopLoss(**2700**) = 2700 in **currency** (default)
• Or SetStopLoss(**1700**) = 1700 in **currency** (asymmetric mode)
take_profit_level:
• SetProfitTarget(**5000**) = 5000 in **currency** (default)
• Or SetProfitTarget(**2200/5400**) = 2200/5400 in **currency** (asymmetric mode)
time_exit_details: Exit at session end time or **CloseAtTime** if specified
function_patterns: PatternFast(49); PatternFast(29); PatternFast(40); PatternFast(52); PatternFast(41); PatternFast(42)
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(49):** closed1>closed2>closed3>closed4 and closed4>closed5
• Meaning: Four consecutive higher closes
• Indicates: Strong upward momentum
• Trading use: Bullish trend confirmation

**PatternFast(29):** body5d > 0.5 * range5d
• Meaning: 5-day body greater than 50% of 5-day range
• Indicates: Strong directional movement over 5 days
• Trading use: Momentum filter

**PatternFast(40):** (opend0-lowd0)< (opend1-lowd1)
• Meaning: Current bar's lower shadow smaller than previous
• Indicates: Reduced downside pressure
• Trading use: Support strength indicator

**PatternFast(52):** highd1<highd2 and lowd1<lowd2
• Meaning: Inside day pattern (lower high and lower low)
• Indicates: Consolidation/indecision
• Trading use: Pattern filter to avoid weak setups

**PatternFast(41):** (opend0-lowd0)> (opend1-lowd1)*0.5
• Meaning: Current lower shadow > 50% of previous lower shadow
• Indicates: Increased downside rejection
• Trading use: Support/buying pressure confirmation

**PatternFast(42):** (opend0-lowd0)> (opend1-lowd1)*1
• Meaning: Current lower shadow > previous lower shadow
• Indicates: Strong downside rejection
• Trading use: Strong support confirmation
number_of_patterns: 6 primary patterns with complex boolean logic
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Sophisticated pattern filtering system reduces false breakouts
• Flexible session-based level calculation
• Asymmetric risk management allows different stops/targets per side
• Multiple time-based exit mechanisms
• Position sizing and trade frequency controls
• Seasonal/day-of-week filtering capabilities

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Extremely complex entry logic may overfit
• High number of parameters increases optimization risk
• Pattern dependencies not clearly documented
• Stop-limit order logic adds execution complexity
• May miss valid breakouts due to excessive filtering

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Fixed currency-based stops (2700 default, 1700 asymmetric)
• Reasonable profit targets with asymmetric sizing
• Maximum trades per day (1) prevents overtrading
• Time-based exits prevent indefinite holding
• Position-aware stop/target setting

**OVERALL:**
A **highly sophisticated breakout system** with extensive pattern filtering. While the complexity may lead to overfitting, the **robust risk management** and **flexible parameter structure** show professional development. The **asymmetric profit targets** (2200 vs 5400) suggest short trades are expected to be more profitable, which is logical for breakout failures.

tags: Conditional Pattern-Based Breakout
summary: This is a **long-only breakout strategy** that trades on Tuesday-Thursday (dayofweek 1-3) during specific time windows. It enters long positions when **PatternFast(23)** consolidation pattern is TRUE and **PatternFast(31)** gap pattern is FALSE, buying at the highest high of the last 16 bars.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Time window: 16:00-21:45 (avoiding 12:00-11:00 pause)
• Maximum 1 entry per day
• Trading days: Tuesday-Thursday only (dayofweek 1-3)
• PatternFast(23) = TRUE (consolidation pattern)
• PatternFast(31) = FALSE (no significant gap up)
• Entry: Buy at highest(H, 16) stop - breakout above 16-bar high
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Time exit at 21:45 on Wednesday only (when currentDayOfWeek = 3)

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 2000 in currency
• Take profit: 8000 in currency
• Breakeven: Disabled (0)

**Time Exits:**
• Forced exit at 21:45 on Wednesday
time_exit_details: Exit at **21:45** on Wednesday only
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(23):** body5d < 0.1 * range5d
• Meaning: 5-day body (open[5] to close[1]) is less than 10% of 5-day range
• Indicates: Extreme consolidation over 5 sessions
• Trading use: Breakout setup - market coiled for potential move

**PatternFast(31):** (highd0-opend0) > (highd1-opend1)*0.25
• Meaning: Today's gap up is more than 25% of yesterday's gap up
• Indicates: Significant gap up continuation
• Trading use: Filter to avoid entering on large gaps (used as FALSE condition)
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Well-defined risk management with 2000 stop and 8000 target (4:1 R/R)
• Combines consolidation setup with gap filter for quality entries
• Restricts trading to mid-week sessions (Tuesday-Thursday)
• Uses breakout methodology above 16-bar high
• Includes position limits (1 entry per day)

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Long-only strategy misses short opportunities
• Very restrictive time windows may miss good setups
• Complex day-of-week logic could be over-optimized
• No breakeven protection despite large profit target
• Gap filter (Pattern 31) might be too restrictive

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Fixed 2000 currency stop loss provides clear risk control
• 8000 profit target offers good reward potential
• Position sizing controlled via MyContracts input
• Daily entry limits prevent overtrading

**OVERALL:**
This is a **solid intermediate-level breakout strategy** with good risk management principles. The combination of consolidation detection and gap filtering shows thoughtful market analysis, but the restrictive time/day filters may limit opportunities. The **4:1 reward-to-risk ratio** is attractive if win rate supports profitability.

tags: Previous Day High/Low and Pre-Market Level Breakout with EMA Trend Filter
summary: A sophisticated **intraday breakout strategy** that trades breakouts of key levels (PDH, PDL, PMH, PML) with **EMA trend confirmation** and **retest validation**. Uses historical support/resistance arrays for dynamic profit targets and combines **trailing stops** with fixed stops for risk management.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• Breakout above PDH or PMH with retest confirmation
• EMA13 > EMA48 > EMA200 (bullish trend alignment)
• Close > EMA13 (price above fast EMA)
• Close > PDL (above previous day low)
• During regular trading session (930-1600)
• Within trading window (930-1200)
• Pattern filter: PatternFast(152) = true AND PatternFast(153) = false

**SHORT Entries:**
• Breakout below PDL or PML with retest confirmation
• EMA13 < EMA48 < EMA200 (bearish trend alignment)
• Close < EMA13 (price below fast EMA)
• Close < PDH (below previous day high)
• During regular trading session (930-1600)
• Within trading window (930-1200)
• Pattern filter: PatternFast(152) = true AND PatternFast(153) = false
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• Trailing stop: Exit when Close crosses EMA13 with epsilon buffer
• End of session: Exit 10 minutes before market close (1550)

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Fixed stop loss: Above/below broken level + epsilon
• Partial profit target: 50% position at next historical resistance (longs) or support (shorts)
• Global stop loss: 10,000 in currency

**Time Exits:**
• Mandatory exit at 1550 (10 minutes before session end)
• Sequence timeout: 60 minutes after breakout if no retest
stop_loss_level:
• SetStopLoss(**10000**) = 10,000 in **currency**
• Additional: Fixed stop at broken level ± EpsilonSupport (0.02)
• Trailing: EMA13 ± EpsilonSupport
take_profit_level:
• Dynamic target from historical support/resistance arrays
• Partial exit: 50% of position at next significant level
• No fixed point-based targets
time_exit_details: Exit at **15:50** (10 minutes before regular session end)
pattern_details:
**PatternFast(152):** true
• Meaning: Always returns true
• Indicates: No pattern restriction
• Trading use: Neutral filter allowing all trades

**PatternFast(153):** false (case >152)
• Meaning: Always returns false for numbers > 152
• Indicates: Invalid pattern number
• Trading use: Used as negative filter (must be false to trade)

**_OHLCMulti5():** Session OHLC calculator
• Meaning: Calculates session-based OHLC values for last 5 sessions
• Indicates: Provides historical price data for pattern analysis
• Trading use: Feeds data to PatternFast function for technical analysis
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• Sophisticated level identification using historical support/resistance arrays
• Multiple confirmation layers: breakout + retest + EMA alignment
• Dynamic profit targets based on historical levels
• Proper session time filtering and pre-market data integration
• Multiple exit strategies: trailing, fixed stops, and time-based
• Risk controls: max trades per day, position sizing, global stop

**WEAKNESSES:**
• Extremely complex with nested loops that could cause performance issues
• Pattern filters are essentially meaningless (152=true, 153=false always)
• Overly complicated level calculation with potential for bugs
• Hard-coded timeframes may not suit all instruments
• Complex retest logic might miss valid setups
• No consideration for market volatility or volume

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Good: Multiple stop loss layers (fixed, trailing, global)
• Good: Position sizing controls and daily trade limits
• Concern: Very high global stop loss (10,000) may be excessive
• Good: Time-based exits prevent overnight exposure

**OVERALL:**
This is a **highly sophisticated but overly complex** strategy that attempts to combine many good concepts. The core logic of trading **PDH/PDL breakouts with EMA confirmation** is sound, but the implementation is unnecessarily complicated. The strategy would benefit from **significant simplification** while retaining the core breakout and trend filter concepts. The pattern filters add no value and the complex level calculations could be streamlined.

tags: RSI Oversold/Overbought with Trend Filter
summary: A **mean reversion strategy** based on Larry Connors' RSI-2 approach, using a **3-period RSI** with oversold entries below 25 and overbought exits above 85. Includes a **150-period SMA trend filter** for long-only trades and allows **pyramiding up to 3 contracts**.
entry_conditions:
**LONG Entries:**
• **First Entry:** RSI(3) crosses below 25 AND close > 150-period SMA
• **Second Entry:** RSI(3) < 25 AND current contracts > 0 AND current contracts < 3 (pyramiding)

**SHORT Entries:**
• None (long-only strategy)
exit_conditions:
**Normal Exits:**
• RSI(3) crosses above 85 (sell all contracts)

**Stop/Target Exits:**
• Stop loss: 5000 in currency per contract
• Breakeven: 1000 in currency

**Time Exits:**
• None
time_exit_details: None
pattern_details:
**RSI(3):** 3-period Relative Strength Index
• Meaning: Very short-term momentum oscillator
• Indicates: Extreme overbought (>85) or oversold (<25) conditions
• Trading use: Mean reversion signals with quick reversals

**Average(close, 150):** 150-period Simple Moving Average
• Meaning: Long-term trend filter
• Indicates: Overall market direction
• Trading use: Only take long trades when price is above this level
quality_analysis:
**STRENGTHS:**
• **Proven methodology** based on Larry Connors' research
• **Trend filter** prevents counter-trend trades
• **Pyramiding capability** allows scaling into positions
• **Risk management** with stop loss and breakeven
• **Short timeframe RSI** for quick mean reversion signals

**WEAKNESSES:**
• **Long-only bias** misses short opportunities
• **No profit target** relies purely on RSI exit signal
• **Fixed stop loss** doesn't adapt to volatility
• **Pyramiding risk** can amplify losses in trending markets

**RISK MANAGEMENT:**
• Stop loss: 5000 currency units provides downside protection
• Breakeven: 1000 currency units locks in small profits
• Position sizing: Limited to 3 contracts maximum

**OVERALL:**
A **solid mean reversion strategy** with good risk controls. The **RSI(3) parameter** creates very sensitive signals for quick reversals. **Trend filter is essential** for this approach. Strategy appears well-tested with **in-sample 2005-2023** and **out-of-sample validation**.
